INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8,3,'2015-07-06 16:32:57','2015-07-06 16:32:57','','Team Members','','publish','closed','closed','','8','','','2015-07-06 20:28:30','2015-07-06 20:28:30','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=cptm&#038;p=8',0,'cptm','',0),(9,3,'2015-07-06 16:42:09','2015-07-06 20:42:09','Gloria Bell brings over 30 years of successful business operations, communications, event management, and entrepreneurial experience, to her roles as Co-Founder and Operations Director of The Women In Tech Summit and as the Marketing Director of TechGirlz.\r\n\r\nIn addition to these roles, Gloria provides social media strategy consulting services to businesses and non-profits as the Chief Digital Strategist at Bell Digital Strategies. She is a frequent speaker on a multitude of social media topics and has been a guest lecturer and Adjunct Professor of Social Media Strategy at Drexel University. Between her current roles and her corporate career, Gloria founded Red Stapler Consulting where she worked with businesses and technology startups providing them with business process and operations consulting and social media strategy and implementation.\r\n\r\nGloria is known as a passionate social media practitioner, entrepreneur, and volunteer. Demonstrating her commitment to the social media and entrepreneurial community, Gloria has served on the Chapter Board of Social Media Club Philadelphia and on the Philly StartUp Leaders Leadership Team as the Events Director. She also serves on the board of the tech incubator Seed Philly, as an instructor and advisor for GirlDevelopIt, as a mentor for Lean Startup Machine and Startup Weekend, and as organizer of PodCamp Philly, PodCamp East and Content Camp.\r\n\r\nWhen she is not working to build and grow the community of women in technology, learning more about writing code, studying the latest technology in the social media marketing space, or tweeting away as <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gloriabell\" target=\"_blank\">@gloriabell</a>, she is behind the lens of her camera, in the kitchen baking, digging in her garden, or spending time with friends and\r\n','Gloria Bell','','publish','closed','closed','','gloria-bell','','','2015-10-19 20:35:22','2015-10-20 00:35:22','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=team&#038;p=9',0,'team','',0),(10,3,'2015-07-06 16:44:21','2015-07-06 20:44:21','“A connection-maker, networking strategist and expert community manager, Kelly Hoey is recognized for her “boots on the ground” leadership in the startup community by her investment in and promotion of women in tech. In 2011 Kelly co-founded Women Innovate Mobile, LLC (WIM), the first startup accelerator focused exclusively on fast-tracking the growth of early-stage mobile technology ventures with gender-diverse founding teams. In 2014, Kelly assumed an interim operations role as Chief Marketing Officer of Cuurio, a New York City based startup. Kelly continues to invest in as well as advise emerging technology companies and sits on the boards of Glimpse, JuiceLabs and Tampa Bay WaVE. She is a mentor for several startup accelerators (Straight Shot, Entrepreneurs Roundtable Accelerator, Grand Central Tech, NYC Venture Fellows) and is an advisor to startups Cuurio, Rchery and GenoStyle. Kelly is Chief Tech Ambassador for the YWCA of NYC’s Geek Girls initiative.\r\nAs managing director of WIM, Kelly was responsible for building the accelerator’s global influencer network of partnerships and connections offline and online (over 100,000 online connections, including 85,000 followers on Google+). She was also responsible for leading WIM’s marketing efforts including creating the Founders Breakfast networking events, Google+ Hangout on Air series #womenwhotech and the “Meet The Innovators” speaker series launched with Apple, Inc. in the SoHo Retail Store in February 2013.\r\nKelly has presented in front of members of the European Commission (on building startup communities) and at conferences/events such as SXSW, IEEE Women in Leadership, PGA Championship, Women In The Boardroom, Bank of America, IIBN, MoDev, Morris County Chamber / Women In Business and Disruptors (Dublin), Walter Cronkite School of Journalism and Meet The Innovators events at the Apple Stores in San Francisco, Chicago and London.\r\nIn 2014, Kelly launched her “In Conversation With…” blog interviewing women entrepreneurs on SharpHeels. She’s appeared on CNBC Power Pitch, NPR and Huffington Post (Live) and has been featured in The New Yorker, Inc., FT, Forbes, Fast Company, WSJ, Business Insider, eWeek, Business Observer (FL), New York Times, Vancouver Sun and other media outlets.”\r\n','Kelly Hoey','','publish','closed','closed','','kelly-hoey','','','2015-10-19 20:36:08','2015-10-20 00:36:08','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=team&#038;p=10',0,'team','',0),(11,3,'2015-07-06 16:49:03','2015-07-06 20:49:03','Tracey is the founder of TechGirlz. She is also a founding member of, and Chief Marketing Officer for, Chariot Solutions, a Philadelphia-based Java and open source software development and consulting firm. Tracey has created the branding and marketing strategy for Chariot, helping it to grow from 10 employees in 2002 to 50. She is also responsible for managing the strategic planning process, as well as spearheading Chariot’s sales efforts.\r\n\r\nAfter graduating from Drexel, Tracey started her career in retail management and advertising sales. She learned about lead development, marketing, and distribution in these roles, but what she really learned was that she’s an entrepreneur at heart. In 1996, Tracey bought a New Jersey-based child transportation company called KangaKab. In 1999, with revenues at $2.5 million and having started a branch in Pennsylvania, Tracey sold KangaKab. As the director of sales & marketing for accounting software provider Skylight Systems, Tracey developed and executed marketing and channel efforts around one of the first-ever hosted accounting products. This program supplemented the existing sales of RFS, Skylight’s server based flagship product. It was very early on for the web-hosted software concept, but several firms began to use this product for their clients.\r\n\r\nTracey is also the founder and current chair of the Emerging Technologies for the Enterprise Conference, (ETE), which is held in Philadelphia each year. ETE attracts world-renowned thought leaders in cutting-edge technologies and serves as a community forum for regional technology companies. Tracey is one of the founding board members of Philadelphia Startup Leaders, a regional organization dedicated to growing technology startup businesses (www.phillystartupleaders.org).','Tracey Welson-Rossman','','publish','closed','closed','','tracey-welson-rossman','','','2015-10-19 20:37:25','2015-10-20 00:37:25','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=team&#038;p=11',0,'team','',0),(12,3,'2015-07-06 19:07:04','2015-07-06 19:07:04','','Team','','publish','closed','closed','','team','','','2015-10-12 10:58:43','2015-10-12 14:58:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(13,3,'2015-07-06 19:08:09','2015-07-06 19:08:09',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','13','','','2016-06-01 20:06:28','2016-06-02 00:06:28','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?p=13',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(15,3,'2015-07-07 01:42:04','2015-07-07 01:42:04','','City','','publish','closed','closed','','15','','','2015-07-08 13:46:27','2015-07-08 17:46:27','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=cptm_tax&#038;p=15',0,'cptm_tax','',0),(16,3,'2015-07-07 01:51:58','2015-07-07 01:51:58','helping with website','Lisa B. Snyder','','publish','closed','closed','','lisa-b-snyder','','','2015-07-07 01:51:58','2015-07-07 01:51:58','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?post_type=team&#038;p=16',0,'team','',0),(17,3,'2015-07-07 02:02:00','2015-07-07 02:02:00','','Become a Sponsor','','publish','closed','closed','','become-a-sponsor','','','2015-10-12 10:58:42','2015-10-12 14:58:42','',0,'http://womenintechs.wpengine.com/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(19,6,'2015-07-07 02:07:40','2015-07-07 06:07:40','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Women in Tech Summit is a series of events that inspire, educate and connect women in the technology industry. Our goal is to support the community of women currently working in technology and to help pave the way for women and young women who want to enter the industry.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Women in Tech Summit is the only women in technology conference that provides attendees with a unique combination of deep-dive, hands-on tech workshops; information and discussions about careers in tech and how to pursue them; and connection and networking opportunities with other women in various aspects and careers in technology. The Women in Tech Summit knows that working in tech is not just about coding but about all aspects of careers in technology. The conference works to bring together women in many different types of careers in tech and at every level from students to senior executives.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All profits generated from each event will support the non-profit, </span><a href=\"http://www.techgirlz.org/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TechGirlz.org</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and its ongoing mission to reduce, and hopefully eliminate, the gender gap in computer and other technology occupations. TechGirlz works to empower middle-school age girls to be the next generation of technology leaders by sparking a passion for tech through free hands-on project based workshops.</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each event is produced by The Women in Tech Summit organizers with the assistance of a local volunteer committee. The local committees assist with planning, identifying speakers from the local women in tech community, volunteers and marketing of the event.</span>','About','','