techevent11','','','2015-07-23 13:53:57','2015-07-23 17:53:57','',109,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/PhillyWomeninTechEvent11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(121,3,'2015-07-23 14:19:40','2015-07-23 18:19:40','','year','','publish','closed','closed','','year','','','2015-07-23 14:19:40','2015-07-23 18:19:40','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=cptm_tax&#038;p=121',0,'cptm_tax','',0),(122,3,'2015-07-27 12:35:54','2015-07-27 16:35:54','\"“1 of 5 Women Changing the World of VC/Entrepreneurship” – Forbes\r\n“25 Smartest Women On Twitter” – Fast Company\r\n“100 Most Influential Tech Women On Twitter” – Business Insider\r\n“6 Inspirational Women In Tech” – CraigConnects\r\n“100 NYC Tech Influencers You Need To Know” – AlleyWatch                                                                                                                  If you asked Kelly Hoey in 2009 if she believed any of these descriptions would be used to describe her within the next five years, she would have replied, “are you kidding me?” Fall of 2009 was a pivotal time in Kelly’s career transformation. It was the moment when she ​was inspired to ​stop playing it safe and used her courage to change everything by accepting an opportunity with many unknowns. So how ​can you prepare for career opportunity? Learn how​ ​a nice girl from Victoria, British Columbia, land​ed​ in New York City as an angel investor, board member​, ​​trusted advisor to hot tech startup​s​​ (​after a c​orporate detour through Toronto as a bankruptcy attorney)​ by developing her networks, ​cultivating ​diverse professional relationships,​ building​ a Yes Me Fund and ​finally, taking that ​courageous leap of ​career ​faith.\"','Keynote:​ A Courageous Leap of Career Faith','','publish','closed','closed','','keynote%e2%80%8b-a-courageous-leap-of-career-faith','','','2015-08-14 12:54:10','2015-08-14 16:54:10','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=122',0,'session','',0),(124,3,'2015-07-27 13:58:42','2015-07-27 17:58:42','Whether you’re growing your business, polishing your resume, just entering or re-entering the workforce, you need to think about your digital brand. Learn how to make social media networks from LinkedIn to Twitter to Pinterest work for you, how to develop a content strategy that can help establish you as a thought leader, and how to avoid landmines and trip wires while doing it. Cecily Kellogg’s decade of living her life publicly online can be both an example and a warning in this session dedicated to building your personal brand.','Closing the Confidence Gap: How to Sell Yourself by Building a Digital Brand','','publish','closed','closed','','closing-the-confidence-gap-how-to-sell-yourself-by-building-a-digital-brand','','','2015-08-14 13:08:12','2015-08-14 17:08:12','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=124',0,'session','',0),(125,3,'2015-07-27 14:00:18','2015-07-27 18:00:18','There is an incredible power in women helping women. It’s believed one woman’s success can only lead to another woman’s success. Easier said than done. Many women can remember a time when no one helped them when they needed assistance the most. Others may feel there is only room for one woman at a time. The reality is women make up 50% of the U.S. workforce and we should begin to use that to our advantage! Today’s modern workplace is often complex with input coming from every direction. How can one navigate the roadmap to success with so many mixed messages? Isn’t it about time we begin to reject old stereotypes and for women to help each other succeed at every level? During this panel discussion, learn through the power of peer support, how to expand your professional network by including more women and help change the lives of others at any stage in your career.','Women Helping Women Thrive: How to Support Other Women at Any Level in Your Career','','publish','closed','closed','','women-helping-women-thrive-how-to-support-other-women-at-any-level-in-your-career','','','2015-08-24 16:33:21','2015-08-24 20:33:21','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=125',0,'session','',0),(126,3,'2015-07-27 14:04:15','2015-07-27 18:04:15','Reach beyond your personal limitations and create your own personal board of directors. In this session you will learn how to obtain mentors, sponsors, and engage with influential brands and organizations.','Act Like a Leader, Think Like a Business','','publish','closed','closed','','act-like-a-leader-think-like-a-business','','','2015-08-31 11:39:41','2015-08-31 15:39:41','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=126',0,'session','',0),(127,3,'2015-07-27 14:05:52','2015-07-27 18:05:52','What are the increasing risks of interconnected systems, and what are the utility values? What does it look like to have a job working in the intersection of tech, policy, engineering, and the law? Have the technology advances in the past two decades lived up to the initial promise to transform our lives for the better? Is there anything you should be aware of today that can benefit—or hurt—your career down the road?\r\n\r\nFour women with different backgrounds explain how their work in tech and cybersecurity has shaped their views of the role of government and the importance of innovation, including the experience of being a woman in tech. Merritt is a Cyber Strategist at DHS\' National Cybersecurity & Communications Integration Center navigating between and among public and private sector entities; Maxine is a US Navy Lieutenant Commander at the Pentagon staffing the Chief of Naval Operations; Deborah is a former Bureau Chief at the FCC now managing a consulting practice; and Gabby is an IP lawyer advising high-tech companies and government contractors. We will explain what we wish we knew 10 years ago and 6 months ago, and we will open the floor to questions about why and how we work the way we do.\r\n','Cyber Security - Are you at Risk?','','publish','closed','closed','','cyber-security-are-you-at-risk','','','2015-09-15 21:18:02','2015-09-16 01:18:02','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=127',0,'session','',0),(129,3,'2015-07-27 22:57:37','2015-07-28 02:57:37','Cecily is a natural storyteller with years of public relations, marketing, and digital strategy experience. In 2007, Cecily founded Double Good Media, a boutique agency developing content strategies to help startups, businesses, and executives sharpen their marketing messages and build thought leadership. She’s a reformed blogger, a non-native Philadelphia evangelist, a mother and wife, and a writer with a book in process. She also has a slightly unhealthy relationship with social media and hair much pinker than it should be at her age.','Cecily Kellogg','','publish','closed','closed','','cecily-kellogg','','','2015-11-01 20:38:08','2015-11-02 01:38:08','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=129',0,'speaker','',0),(130,3,'2015-07-27 23:07:09','2015-07-28 03:07:09','A ‘telecom visionary’ according to Marie Claire magazine and vocal advocate for gender and cultural diversity in the tech industry, Ms. Brigitte Daniel is the Executive Vice President of Wilco Electronic Systems, Inc., her family’s African-American privately owned cable operation. For over 30 years, Wilco has provided affordable cable and technology services to low-income communities as well as commercial, governmental, and educational institutions, in Philadelphia.\r\nOver the last few years, Ms. Daniel has helped create several substantial private/public partnerships that provide innovative solutions to address the digital divide within communities in the United States, and thus, position Wilco as a digital and broadband leader, specifically working on behalf of disadvantaged communities.\r\nA 2011 Eisenhower Fellowship recipient, Brigitte traveled to India, Sri Lanka, Singapore and Malaysia to explore and cultivate global relationships in developing emerging technologies to serve and benefit underserved and low-income marketplaces in Philadelphia. In addition, Brigitte is currently serving her second term on the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) Federal Advisory Committee on Diversity in the Digital Age.\r\nIn June 2014, Brigitte was recognized as one of the 7 Brilliant Women in Tech according to Craigslist founder Craig Newmark, was recently featured in Marie Claire magazine as one of three profiles in its “Mogul Maintenance” column, a part of the @Work section for the September 2014 issue, and just launched an initiative called Mogulette, a program centered around educating, mentoring and empowering young women of color, between the ages of 20-25 interested in careers in entrepreneurism within technology.\r\nMs. Daniel graduated from Spelman College in 1999 and additionally received her JD from Georgetown University Law School. In 2011, Ms. Daniel received the Business Journal’s “40 under 40″. In 2012, she was honored to receive the Philadelphia’s Business Journal’s Minority Leaders Award and a 2012 Women Leaders In Technology Award from the National Organization of Black Elected Legislative Women. In 2013, Ms. Daniel received a 2013 Women In Cable and Telecommunications Rising Star Award, a Next Generation of Leaders award through the office of Philadelphia Councilwoman Blondell Reynolds Brown, a “10 under 40” award from the Philadelphia Tribune, and lastly a 2013 Paragon Legacy Award from the Philadelphia chapter of the National Association of Multi-Ethnicity In Communications (NAMIC).\r\nMs. Daniel is committed to giving back to the community and spends a significant amount of time serving as a Board Director of the Philadelphia Theatre Company, Congreso de Latinos, and the Independence Charter School.','Brigitte Daniel','','publish','closed','closed','','brigitte-daniel','','','2015-07-28 23:26:54','2015-07-29 03:26:54','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=130',0,'speaker','',0),(131,3,'2015-07-27 23:10:47','2015-07-28 03:10:47','As an early pioneer of the Internet, Anne Balduzzi has over 25 years of online expertise. Her background includes marketing and product development roles at Apple, AOL (when it was a small start-up), and Viewtron, the first consumer online service in North America. After working in Silicon Valley and launching Apple’s first online service, she returned to the East Coast and founded Accelerate Partners, where she mentored and advised a wide range of early stage and established technology companies and spoke on technology trends. Anne is currently the Founder of SameGrain, an award winning \"privacy first\" social discovery start-up located in Baltimore\'s ETC (Emerging Technology Centers) incubator.','Anne Balduzzi','','publish','closed','closed','','anne-balduzzi','','','2015-08-02 11:14:05','2015-08-02 15:14:05','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=131',0,'speaker','',0),(132,3,'2015-07-28 08:56:22','2015-07-28 12:56:22','<a href=\"https://donnaedwardsforsenate.com/about/\" target=\"_blank\">About Congresswoman Edwards</a>','Congresswoman Donna Edwards','','publish','closed','closed','','congresswoman-donna-edwards','','','2015-09-24 12:19:05','2015-09-24 16:19:05','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=132',0,'speaker','',0),(133,3,'2015-07-28 09:04:12','2015-07-28 13:04:12','','placeholder','','inherit','closed','closed','','placeholder','','','2015-07-28 09:04:27','2015-07-28 13:04:27','',132,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/placeholder.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(134,3,'2015-07-28 10:12:01','2015-07-28 14:12:01','','Sessions','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_sessions-2','','','2015-07-29 12:17:30','2015-07-29 16:17:30','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=134',0,'acf','',0),(136,3,'2015-07-28 13:18:48','2015-07-28 17:18:48','Merritt advises the government in the Department of Homeland Security’s Office of Cybersecurity & Communications. She works in cyber critical infrastructure protection, negotiating between and among private sector and government entities to keep systems running. She also runs a tech firm that provides business strategy to early-stage companies.                                                                                                                                                        Merritt has worked in technology law and policy in all three branches of government, including the US Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces (highest appellate court of the US Military) and the office of US Senator Michael Bennet (D-CO). She speaks regularly on emerging areas including the future of the Internet, corporate interactions with government cyber, women in tech, cybersecurity, Internet law and policy, entrepreneurism and innovation. Her insights on business strategy and tech have been published in Forbes, The Baltimore Sun, Talking Points Memo and ThinkProgress. Her academic work has been published by journals of the University of Virginia, Georgetown, and Santa Clara.                                                                                                             Merritt is a graduate of Harvard College and Harvard Law School. Based in Washington, DC, she is a Fellow at the EastWest Institute, an Adjunct Professor of Cybersecurity at the University of Maryland, and an amateur boxer.','Merritt Baer','','publish','closed','closed','','merritt-baer','','','2015-08-10 18:12:52','2015-08-10 22:12:52','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=136',0,'speaker','',0),(137,3,'2015-07-28 13:28:50','2015-07-28 17:28:50','','Our Series Sponsors','','publish','closed','closed','','our-series-sponsors','','','2015-10-12 10:58:43','2015-10-12 14:58:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=137',0,'page','',0),(139,3,'2015-07-28 14:05:04','2015-07-28 18:05:04','Mobility generates faster response times from clients and coworkers alike. With improved experiences for collaboration, we are collecting data in-the-moment and applying analytics in real-time, which companies are now able to share through the web and mobile apps, enhancing visibility and improving decision making across the organization. In this session, the speaker will address the importance of user experience in mobility, data visualization, and share a vision on the future of connected devices and immersive environments.\r\n','Mobility - Changing the Experience of Enterprise Collaboration','','publish','closed','closed','','mobility-changing-the-course-of-enterprise-communication','','','2015-09-15 21:18:54','2015-09-16 01:18:54','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=139',0,'session','',0),(140,3,'2015-07-28 14:05:57','2015-07-28 18:05:57','Version control is as essential to creating software as track changes is to document collaboration. Git is one of the most popular version control systems available, and repository sites like BitBucket and Github serve as online portfolios for many software engineers. Beyond just being an essential tool to collaborate and keep track of work, Git is also a great way to try new things without losing what you already have with powerful-yet-simple branching and merging capabilities. While it’s an essential tool, it can be hard to get started. This workshop will introduce you to git, from installation all the way up to branching and working out of common problems.','Introduction to Git: Take Chances with a Safety Net','','publish','closed','closed','','introduction-to-git-take-chances-with-a-safety-net','','','2015-09-14 09:20:18','2015-09-14 13:20:18','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=140',0,'session','',0),(141,3,'2015-07-28 21:15:31','2015-07-29 01:15:31','','donna_edwards','','inherit','closed','closed','','donna_edwards','','','2015-07-28 21:15:43','2015-07-29 01:15:43','',132,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/donna_edwards.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(142,3,'2015-07-28 21:16:17','2015-07-29 01:16:17','','Anne_Balduzzi','','inherit','closed','closed','','anne_balduzzi','','','2015-07-28 21:16:25','2015-07-29 01:16:25','',131,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Anne_Balduzzi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(143,3,'2015-07-28 21:17:33','2015-07-29 01:17:33','','Brigitte-Daniel','','inherit','closed','closed','','brigitte-daniel-2','','','2015-07-28 21:17:44','2015-07-29 01:17:44','',130,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Brigitte-Daniel.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(145,3,'2015-07-28 21:19:16','2015-07-29 01:19:16','','Cecily-Kellogg','','inherit','closed','closed','','cecily-kellogg-2','','','2015-07-28 21:19:28','2015-07-29 01:19:28','',129,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Cecily-Kellogg.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(146,3,'2015-07-28 22:27:37','2015-07-29 02:27:37','','Speakers','','publish','closed','closed','','acf_speakers-2','','','2015-08-13 20:06:05','2015-08-14 00:06:05','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=acf&#038;p=146',0,'acf','',0),(148,3,'2015-07-29 17:39:10','2015-07-29 21:39:10','Deb is a Baltimore native living in Roland Park with her husband of four years Peter Savage (co-founder www.passporthealthusa.com). While she calls Baltimore home, most of her career has been spent travelling. She most recently spent time in Dubai, UAE and Jordan working on several entertainment software projects for release in Arabic speaking countries.\r\n\r\nDeb’s early career was in casting talent for radio and television commercials and feature films. This allowed her to make the transition to an advertising agency account executive. In the 1980’s she was part of the thriving Mid-Atlantic advertising scene. She worked with clients at Head Sportswear, Roy Rogers fast food, <em>Washington Times</em> newspaper and many others. From there she started her own advertising photography boutique with a talented partner and fashion photographer, Helen Norman. They worked with mid-Atlantic fashion favorites like Merry-Go-Round, Britches of Georgetown, Webster’s Menswear and more.\r\n\r\nBy the late 80’s Deb felt the call of computer gaming. She joined Microprose Software where she lead the marketing and promotional efforts for one of the greatest computer games of all time; Sid Meier’s Civilization. While there she managed the marketing and promotion for multiple Microprose best sellers, among them Masters of Orion, X-Com, Darklands, F-117A and Gunship 2000. By 1995 Deb spearheaded a joint venture between the ABC network and Microprose Software, called OT Sports. The JV produced ABC Sports branded computer games. <em>The Walt Disney Company</em>eventually acquired the JV in 1998 and Deb found herself drawn to the dot com world for her next career venture.\r\n\r\nBy 1999 Deb helped launch a political activist portal in time for the 2000 Presidential election; SpeakOut.com. Another social networking web site followed; Firewater.com. Deb was Chief Marketing Officer and instrumental in repositioning the company and its technology for an acquisition by a national media firm. After the acquisition, Deb joined the Eager Street Group in 2001 as a consultant and in that capacity joined BreakAway to help grow the company beyond its entertainment roots.\r\n\r\nIn 2002 Deb joined BreakAway full time as president and under her direction grew the company revenue and staff. Deb was instrumental in positioning the company to capitalize on the emerging Serious Games market. Additionally, she was responsible for 2 satellite offices in Texas and the launch of several entertainment software projects in the Middle East.\r\n\r\nDeb’s consulting business is a natural out growth of her years of experience and her desire to offer value added services to passionate entrepreneurs with a “big idea”. She thrives on taking an idea from concept to market. Working along side dedicated, innovative people, Deb is committed to bringing good ideas to market through sound market analysis and long range strategic planning.','Deb Tillett','','publish','closed','closed','','deb-tillet','','','2015-09-20 09:50:50','2015-09-20 13:50:50','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=148',0,'speaker','',0),(149,3,'2015-07-29 19:35:13','2015-07-29 23:35:13','','Gloria Bell','','publish','closed','closed','','gloria-bell','','','2015-08-20 16:21:12','2015-08-20 20:21:12','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=149',0,'speaker','',0),(150,3,'2015-07-29 19:38:34','2015-07-29 23:38:34','','Tracey Welson-Rossman','','publish','closed','closed','','tracey-welson-rossman','','','2015-08-10 21:00:41','2015-08-11 01:00:41','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=150',0,'speaker','',0),(151,3,'2015-07-29 19:43:33','2015-07-29 23:43:33','“A connection-maker, networking strategist and expert community manager, Kelly Hoey is recognized for her “boots on the ground” leadership in the startup community by her investment in and promotion of women in tech. In 2011 Kelly co-founded Women Innovate Mobile, LLC (WIM), the first startup accelerator focused exclusively on fast-tracking the growth of early-stage mobile technology ventures with gender-diverse founding teams. In 2014, Kelly assumed an interim operations role as Chief Marketing Officer of Cuurio, a New York City based startup. Kelly continues to invest in as well as advise emerging technology companies and sits on the boards of Glimpse, JuiceLabs and Tampa Bay WaVE. She is a mentor for several startup accelerators (Straight Shot, Entrepreneurs Roundtable Accelerator, Grand Central Tech, NYC Venture Fellows) and is an advisor to startups Cuurio, Rchery and GenoStyle. Kelly is Chief Tech Ambassador for the YWCA of NYC’s Geek Girls initiative.\r\nAs managing director of WIM, Kelly was responsible for building the accelerator’s global influencer network of partnerships and connections offline and online (over 100,000 online connections, including 85,000 followers on Google+). She was also responsible for leading WIM’s marketing efforts including creating the Founders Breakfast networking events, Google+ Hangout on Air series #womenwhotech and the “Meet The Innovators” speaker series launched with Apple, Inc. in the SoHo Retail Store in February 2013.\r\nKelly has presented in front of members of the European Commission (on building startup communities) and at conferences/events such as SXSW, IEEE Women in Leadership, PGA Championship, Women In The Boardroom, Bank of America, IIBN, MoDev, Morris County Chamber / Women In Business and Disruptors (Dublin), Walter Cronkite School of Journalism and Meet The Innovators events at the Apple Stores in San Francisco, Chicago and London.\r\nIn 2014, Kelly launched her “In Conversation With…” blog interviewing women entrepreneurs on SharpHeels. She’s appeared on CNBC Power Pitch, NPR and Huffington Post (Live) and has been featured in The New Yorker, Inc., FT, Forbes, Fast Company, WSJ, Business Insider, eWeek, Business Observer (FL), New York Times, Vancouver Sun and other media outlets. ','Kelly Hoey','','publish','closed','closed','','kelly-hoey','','','2015-07-29 20:04:20','2015-07-30 00:04:20','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=151',0,'speaker','',0),(155,3,'2015-07-31 09:55:54','2015-07-31 13:55:54','','Large Blog Image','','inherit','closed','closed','','large-blog-image','','','2015-08-02 11:06:13','2015-08-02 15:06:13','',156,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/WITS-600-55bb7e6av1_site_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(156,3,'2015-08-02 11:09:22','2015-08-02 15:09:22','<strong>Connected to event home page</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/WITS-logo-wide-300x83.png\" alt=\"the women in tech summit logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"83\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-60\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/WITS-logo-150x150.png\" alt=\"the women in tech summit logo\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-61\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Connected to Baltimore speakers page</strong>\r\n<a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/baltimore-speakers/\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/WITS-logo-wide-300x83.png\" alt=\"the women in tech summit logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"83\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-60\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/baltimore-speakers/\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/WITS-logo-150x150.png\" alt=\"the women in tech summit logo\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-61\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Connected to Philadelphia speakers page</strong>\r\nComing soon.','Event badges','','publish','closed','closed','','event-badges','','','2015-10-12 10:58:42','2015-10-12 14:58:42','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=156',0,'page','',0),(159,3,'2015-08-06 08:53:23','2015-08-06 12:53:23','<a href=\"http://technical.ly/baltimore/2015/07/31/women-tech-summit-coming-baltimore/?utm_source=%40TechnicallyBMR&utm_medium=twitter&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+startupbaltimore+%28Technically+Baltimore%29\" target=\"_blank\">Read Article</a>','Announcement in Technical.ly Baltimore','','publish','closed','closed','','announcement-in-technical-ly-baltimore','','','2015-08-06 09:16:43','2015-08-06 13:16:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=159',0,'post','',0),(160,3,'2015-08-06 09:14:18','2015-08-06 13:14:18','<div class=\"storify\"><iframe src=\"//storify.com/gloriabell/philly-women-in-tech-summit-2015/embed?header=false&border=false\" width=\"100%\" height=\"750\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\"></iframe><script src=\"//storify.com/gloriabell/philly-women-in-tech-summit-2015.js?header=false&border=false\"></script><noscript>[<a href=\"//storify.com/gloriabell/philly-women-in-tech-summit-2015\" target=\"_blank\">View the story \"Philly Women In Tech Summit 2015\" on Storify</a>]</noscript></div>','Storify recap from Philadelphia event 2015','','publish','closed','closed','','storify-recap-from-philadelphia-event-2015','','','2015-08-06 09:14:18','2015-08-06 13:14:18','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=160',0,'post','',0),(161,3,'2015-08-06 09:04:42','2015-08-06 13:04:42','','News','','publish','closed','closed','','news','','','2015-10-12 10:58:43','2015-10-12 14:58:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=161',0,'page','',0),(162,3,'2015-08-06 09:17:54','2015-08-06 13:17:54',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','162','','','2016-06-01 20:06:28','2016-06-02 00:06:28','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=162',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(163,3,'2015-08-06 13:50:07','2015-08-06 17:50:07','','techgirlzlogo','','inherit','closed','closed','','techgirlzlogo','','','2015-08-06 13:50:23','2015-08-06 17:50:23','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/techgirlzlogo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(164,3,'2015-08-06 14:05:47','2015-08-06 18:05:47','<a href=\"http://technical.ly/philly/2015/08/03/women-in-tech-summit-expansion/\" target=\"_blank\">Read the announcement: Philly’s Women in Tech Summit is expanding to 3 other cities</a>\r\n','Announcement from Technical.ly Philly','','publish','closed','closed','','announcement-from-technical-ly-philly','','','2015-08-06 14:06:16','2015-08-06 18:06:16','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=164',0,'post','',0),(165,3,'2015-08-06 14:08:51','2015-08-06 18:08:51','FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE\r\nContact:  Mason Luvera\r\n360-632-4692\r\nmluvera@slicecommunications.com\r\n\r\nThe Women in Tech Summit Announces 2015 Conference in Baltimore\r\n\r\nOrganization expanding to reach new communities of women in technology based on success of its annual Philadelphia Summit\r\n\r\nJuly 30, 2015 (Philadelphia) – The Women in Tech Summit, a series of annual events that inspire, educate and connect women in the technology industry, announced today the addition of a new 2015 summit in Baltimore. The Baltimore Women in Tech Summit will be the first event outside of the organization’s native Philadelphia, and introduces the next phase for the conference as it expands to bring the event’s valuable content to new regions.\r\n\r\nThe 2015 Baltimore Women in Tech Summit will run from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. on Sept. 26 at the University of Baltimore Business Center, and is sponsored by the University of Baltimore Merrick School of Business. The event will kick off with an opening keynote by connection-maker, networking strategist and expert community manager Kelly Hoey, who is the co-founder of Women Innovate Mobile, LLC (WIM), the first startup accelerator focused exclusively on fast-tracking the growth of early-stage mobile technology ventures with gender-diverse founding teams.   Following the keynote speech, will be a full day of additional speaker sessions, workshops and a networking lunch.\r\n\r\n“There’s a large gap in the technology industry for women,” said Gloria Bell, Operations Director of the Women in Tech Summit. “For women already in the tech field or young women looking to enter the industry, the Summit is an exceptional way to find a supportive group of professional, like-minded women sharing the same journey.” \r\n\r\nFounder of TechGirlz, a non-profit organization dedicated to empowering girls to become future technology leaders, and also the chief marketing officer at Chariot Solutions, Tracey Welson-Rossman created the Women in Tech Summit four years ago as a way to get Philadelphia-area women in technology together to talk about all the important things that were missing in the current technology conference market.  \r\n\r\n“The Philadelphia Women in Tech Summit has been so successful over the past four years, bringing technology-focused women from all over the region together to learn and share ideas,” said Welson-Rossman. “It provides real, actionable opportunities for women to further their careers in tech with hands-on workshops, networking and in-depth discussions that delve into what really matters for women in this industry.” \r\n\r\nOne of the very few women-in-technology conferences available, the Women in Tech Summit provides attendees with insight and opportunities uniquely tailored to the needs of women working in the technology industry. Each summit includes deep, hands-on workshops, information and discussions about careers in tech and how to pursue them, as well as networking opportunities with other women.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Women in Tech Summit was first held in Philadelphia in 2011, and attracted an attendance of 150 local professionals in technology. This year, the 2015 Philadelphia Summit sold out with 325 people in attendance, and had a waiting list surpassing 250 individuals. The success of the event in Philadelphia, combined with strong attendee requests, sparked the event’s expansion to add the new Baltimore Summit.\r\n\r\n“By expanding to new regions, we are able to bring together strong, local, women-centered technology communities in areas where we know women can both benefit and contribute to the amazing content the Women in Tech Summit provides,” Bell said. “The success of the Philadelphia Summit proved just how much desire and support there is for these events.”\r\n\r\nEach summit is produced by The Women in Tech Summit organization alongside a local volunteer committee in the specific summit’s region. Each local committee assists with planning the event, securing speakers from the local women in tech community, and managing the marketing of the event to ensure it meets the needs of each region. \r\n\r\nAll profits generated from each summit will support the non-profit TechGirlz and its ongoing mission to reduce and eliminate the gender gap in computer and other technology occupations. TechGirlz hosts free and fun hands-on workshops to empower middle-school age girls to be the next generation of technology leaders.\r\n\r\nTickets for the Baltimore Women in Tech Summit are available for purchase through the summit’s website at http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/baltimore/.\r\n\r\nAbout The Women in Tech Summit\r\nA series of annual, multi-location events, The Women in Tech Summit works to inspire, educate and connect women in the technology industry.  Each event is organized with the goal to support the community of women currently working in technology and to help pave the way for women and young women who want to enter the industry. By providing attendees with a unique combination of in-depth, hands-on tech workshops; discussions about careers in tech and how to pursue them; and networking opportunities with other women in technology, The Women in Tech Summit provides a venue to bring together and empower women across the technology industry. For more information about the summit or to register for an upcoming summit, visit the website at www.womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com.\r\n','The Women in Tech Summit Announces 2015 Conference in Baltimore','','publish','closed','closed','','the-women-in-tech-summit-announces-2015-conference-in-baltimore','','','2015-08-06 14:08:51','2015-08-06 18:08:51','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=165',0,'post','',0),(166,3,'2015-08-06 17:00:34','2015-08-06 21:00:34','One of Forbes Top 10 Female Entrepreneurs to Watch and the mom of four boys, Founder of Colliders Accelerator, AboutOne (the world’s only Family Management Cloud Platform) and a board adviser to Flex-IT (an \"Uber for Tech contractors\"), Joanne Lang writes and speaks regularly on topics including entrepreneurship, fundraising, business development, networking, and leveraging technology to simplify life and prepare for the future.\r\n\r\nLang has appeared first on stage at VentureBeat DEMO and is one of the 3% of women who have raised $5M in capital in the US. She is and was featured in Microsoft’s documentary, CTRL+ALT+COMPETE. She’s a 2014 SmartCEO Voltage Award finalist, A Dell Founders Club Entrepreneur, and blogs for Huffington Post, The Wall Street Journal, Women 2.0, and Region’s Business. Lang is also a frequent panelist, including the NYU Women Entrepreneurs Festival, CES Living in Digital Times, Women 2.0 Founder <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_538667973\"><span class=\"aQJ\">Friday</span></span>, Women in Tech Summit, and BlogHer Entrepreneurs.  Lang is also a 2015 judge for \"The Stevie Awards\" for Women-In-Business.\r\n\r\nWith the support of AWE [<a href=\"http://www.phillyawe.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.phillyawe.org</a>] and Gartner, Joanne recently founded Colliders Accelerator, which offers a unique opportunity for women entrepreneurs’ to receive the customized mentoring they need to refine and launch their business ideas. The accelerator provides in-person and virtual educational sessions, as well as resources and funding assistance to build technology and run marketing and PR programs.  What really sets Colliders apart is their corporate matchmaking service that gives entrepreneurs an opportunity to find the perfect corporate business match and early access to customer revenue, investment or acquisition potential, while in-parallel providing a \"Virtual Innovation Center\" for corporations.','Joanne Lang','','publish','closed','closed','','joanne-lang','','','2015-09-22 10:20:34','2015-09-22 14:20:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=166',0,'speaker','',0),(167,3,'2015-08-06 17:05:46','2015-08-06 21:05:46','Margaret Roth is the Chief Marketing Officer and Co-Founder of Yet Analytics. Based in Baltimore, MD, the firm builds software that helps organizations leverage advanced data and analytics for the purpose of improving human capital.                                                                                                                     As CMO, Margaret oversees marketing and development strategy, operational and administrative projects, and client and partner relationships.                    Through her many leadership roles Margaret has extensive experience with leadership development, team facilitation, brand development, marketing strategy, and event organization.                                                                                                                                                                                                   In addition to serving on the Junior League of Baltimore\'s Board of Directors as the Vice President of Community Impact, Margaret is the co-founder of EdTechWomen, an international networked community for women\'s leadership in education technology, a mentor for the ETC\'s AccelerateBaltimore entrepreneurs program, a member of the SXSWedu LAUNCHedu Advisory Board, and a volunteer American Canoe Association Whitewater Kayaking and swift-water rescue instructor at Johns Hopkins University. She is a die-hard Blue Jay Lacrosse fan, and spends a lot of time cooking, writing, organizing, and exploring.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Margaret graduated from The Johns Hopkins University with her Master of Arts in Teaching in May 2012 with certifications in Secondary English, Middle School English Language Arts, and Middle School Science. She also earned her Bachelor of Arts degrees from JHU in English and Environmental Earth Science.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Margaret has been recognized in 2015 by the Daily Record as one of Maryland\'s 20 in Their Twenties and by SXSWedu as a Change Maker of the Year.','Margaret Roth','','publish','closed','closed','','margaret-roth','','','2015-08-27 19:28:20','2015-08-27 23:28:20','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=167',0,'speaker','',0),(168,3,'2015-08-08 14:39:14','2015-08-08 18:39:14','','Joanne_Lang','','inherit','closed','closed','','joanne_lang300dpi','','','2015-08-08 14:39:33','2015-08-08 18:39:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Joanne_Lang@300dpi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(169,3,'2015-06-08 22:31:12','2015-06-09 02:31:12','<a href=\"http://www.semrush.com/blog/4-things-i-learned-at-the-2015-philly-women-in-tech-summit/\" target=\"_blank\">Read the article in SEMRUSH</a>','4 things I learned at the 2015 Philly Women in Tech Summit','','publish','closed','closed','','4-things-i-learned-at-the-2015-philly-women-in-tech-summit','','','2016-03-02 10:39:08','2016-03-02 15:39:08','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=169',0,'post','',0),(170,3,'2015-04-27 22:32:38','2015-04-28 02:32:38','<a href=\"http://technical.ly/philly/2015/04/27/4-rules-women-in-tech-summit/\" target=\"_blank\">Read the article on Technicl.ly Philly</a>','4 rules every female entrepreneur should live by','','publish','closed','closed','','4-rules-every-female-entrepreneur-should-live-by','','','2016-03-02 10:37:43','2016-03-02 15:37:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=170',0,'post','',0),(171,3,'2015-08-09 22:34:34','2015-08-10 02:34:34','<a href=\"http://sharpheels.com/2015/04/keeping-your-wits-in-tech/\" target=\"_blank\">Read the article on Sharp Heels</a>','Keeping your WITS in Tech','','publish','closed','closed','','keeping-your-wits-in-tech','','','2015-08-09 22:34:34','2015-08-10 02:34:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=171',0,'post','',0),(172,3,'2015-08-09 22:36:15','2015-08-10 02:36:15','<a href=\"http://us4.campaign-archive1.com/?u=c0eaad85c7353d43277950b62&id=4f83b823a8&e=139b07e9a3\" target=\"_blank\">Read the article from Kelly Hoey</a>','Innovator Insights from Kelly Hoey','','publish','closed','closed','','innovator-insights-from-kelly-hoey','','','2015-08-09 22:36:15','2015-08-10 02:36:15','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=172',0,'post','',0),(173,3,'2015-08-09 22:39:48','2015-08-10 02:39:48','<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/glokbell/sets/72157651998451166\" target=\"_blank\">View Photos from April 2015 event </a>','Photos from Philly Women in Tech 2015','','publish','closed','closed','','photos-from-philly-women-in-tech-2015','','','2015-08-09 22:39:48','2015-08-10 02:39:48','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=173',0,'post','',0),(174,3,'2015-08-10 17:48:26','2015-08-10 21:48:26','','Merritt_Baer','','inherit','closed','closed','','merrittbaer','','','2015-08-10 17:48:39','2015-08-10 21:48:39','',136,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/MerrittBaer.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(175,3,'2015-08-10 18:22:56','2015-08-10 22:22:56','Katherine Garcia is part of the founding team for the Center for Open Data Enterprise, where she manages communications and outreach. Previously she worked at The Governance Lab at New York University and the U.S. Mission to the United Nations. Katherine earned her MPA with an emphasis in Policy Analysis from Baruch College. She has over 10 years of media and publishing experience.                                                                                                       Katherine is an active member of the Metro New York Chapter of the U.S. National Committee for UN Women and was elected Co-President in 2014. The chapter aims to increase public, political and financial support for UN Women, the United Nations entity for gender equality and women\'s empowerment. She is a Board Director for SustainUS, a non-profit that empowers young people to advance sustainable development. She also organizes the Washington Viz-ards, a meetup group for data visualization enthusiasts in DC.','Katherine Garcia','','publish','closed','closed','','katherine-garcia','','','2015-08-10 18:26:37','2015-08-10 22:26:37','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=175',0,'speaker','',0),(176,3,'2015-08-11 10:16:03','2015-08-11 14:16:03','Gabriella provides full service intellectual property strategic guidance to her clients in a wide range of industries spanning from high technology companies to government contractors. Her multifaceted experience in the tech community allows her to bring a holistic perspective to her problem solving approach. Gabriella\'s seen the tech industry from all sides: serving as outside counsel, working in-house at technology companies in Silicon Valley, advising tech-start ups, clerking for a magistrate judge, and bringing the technology community together by organizing symposia, publishing opportunities, and mentoring programs. Prior to her career in tech, Gabriella worked closely with the Arizona Board of Regents as an advocate for higher education, women\'s rights, and LGBTQ rights initiatives in her capacity as Vice President of the University of Arizona.','Gabriella Ziccarelli','','publish','closed','closed','','gabriella-ziccarelli','','','2015-08-11 10:16:03','2015-08-11 14:16:03','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=176',0,'speaker','',0),(177,3,'2015-08-16 19:43:42','2015-08-16 23:43:42','Deborah Lathen is an accomplished corporate attorney, business leader, domestic and international policy advisor. Lathen has enjoyed a distinguished career in both the private and public sectors, having held a senior executive position with the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), legal and senior management positions with national law firms and Fortune 500 corporations, including The Quaker Oats Company, TRW and Nissan Motor Corporation USA. In February 2007 she was named a director of British Telecom, a FTSE 50 and global telecommunications company where she was a member of the Remunerations and the Committee for Responsible and Sustainable Business. She completed her term in 2010. In July 2011 she was appointed by the Mayor of the District of Columbia to the newly created District of Columbia Board of Ethics and Accountability where she serves as a member of the board.\r\n\r\nIn 2001 Lathen established Lathen Consulting, LLC which specializes in providing policy, legal, and advisory services to high tech, telecommunications and media companies. Her client list includes Fortune 500 companies, such as Scientific-Atlanta, a Cisco company, Verizon Communications, AT&amp;T and others.\r\n\r\nLathen was appointed Chief of the FCC’s Cable Services Bureau in May 1998 where she led a 100+ team of lawyers, economists and engineers in helping to craft today’s converged digital and broadband landscape. Lathen provided legal, policy and regulatory guidance to the FCC chairman and commissioners on cable, broadband, video programming and Internet industries as the agency spurred the development of the then-nascent broadband marketplace. As Chief of the Cable Bureau, Lathen presided over some of the most groundbreaking regulatory and merger proceedings that shape the way consumers access the Internet, place phone calls, and receive video programming. She supervised the analysis and review of several high-profile mergers, including AT&amp;T’s acquisition of TCI and the merger of AOL and Time Warner.\r\n\r\nUnder her direction, the Cable Bureau published a number of landmark reports, including Broadband Today, a comprehensive report on the state of the broadband industry that contained policy recommendations that helped foster the explosive growth of the industry. Lathen regularly interfaces with the telephone, video, cable and broadcast industries and is frequently invited to speak at industry conferences and panels, such as the Practising Law Institute, the National Cable Association Annual Conference, and the British American Business Association. She has also lectured at Duke University, the University of Washington and Howard University.\r\n\r\nA regulatory expert on telecommunications issues, Lathen has testified before the U.S. Congress and the National Governors Association. She was a keynote 2 speaker at a Financial Times conference in London, where she detailed the rollout of advanced telecommunications services in the U.S. Lathen was a keynote speaker at the Second Annual Sino-American Cable Convergence Conference in Beijing China and was a representative of the U.S. telecommunications regulator in meetings with high-ranking Chinese government officials on cable and other communications issues. She has appeared on CNN Financial News and C-Span as an expert on cable and telecommunications issues.\r\n\r\nDuring her 8-year tenure at Nissan Motor Corporation in Carson, California, Lathen was the first African-American woman to serve as a senior manager. She was Director of National Consumer Affairs, where she was commended for reorganizing and instituting customer service initiatives that improved customer satisfaction levels, enhanced employee morale and increased brand loyalty. While at Nissan, Lathen also was a member of the Legal Department management team holding the position of Managing Counsel. In that role, Lathen supervised the Business Transactions Group, which was responsible for providing a full complement of legal services to Nissan and its North American affiliates. She developed and implemented the company’s antitrust training and environmental law compliance programs. Lathen also led the legal team that successfully negotiated the first and largest joint product development agreement between Nissan Motor Corporation and the Ford Motor Company. Prior to Nissan, Lathen was Senior Counsel at TRW in Orange, California where she specialized in transactional and litigation matters. Early in her legal career, Lathen served as a litigation attorney with The Quaker Oats Company in Chicago, Illinois. Lathen was also an associate with Foley and Lardner in Milwaukee, Wisconsin and with Keck, Mahin and Cate in Chicago, Illinois.\r\n\r\nThroughout her career, Lathen has worked with a diverse range of non-profit entities. Currently, she serves on the Minorities in Telecommunications and Communications (MMTC), a telecommunications civil rights group. Prior board memberships include Rails to Trails National Conservancy, which converts unused railroad tracks into biking and recreational paths, Safe Harbor Shelter for homeless women and children in Los Angeles, California. Lathen was also instrumental in establishing the Nissan Foundation, serving as the Foundation\'s Secretary for a five-year period. The foundation provided grants to small business and community organizations for the development of inner city areas of Los Angeles.\r\n\r\nLathen was born in St. Louis, Missouri and was raised in the suburbs of Chicago, Illinois. She received a Juris Doctor from Harvard Law School and a Bachelor of Arts, magna cum laude, in Government with Distinction in All Subjects from Cornell University. She is a member of the California, Illinois and Wisconsin State Bar Associations.','Deborah Lathen','','publish','closed','closed','','deborah-lathen','','','2015-08-25 15:45:15','2015-08-25 19:45:15','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=177',0,'speaker','',0),(178,3,'2015-08-16 19:39:52','2015-08-16 23:39:52','Maxine is a logistician and operations research subject matter expert for the Chief of Naval Operation\'s Staff in the Pentagon under the Combat Logistics and Transportation Mobility Division.  She applies scientific principles and quantitative analysis to inform recommendations to Navy leadership for solving complex problems. Maxine served aboard USS SAN JACINTO (CG 56) and USS HIGGINS (DDG 76) deploying twice to the Middle East. Maxine also participated in the source selection for a multi-billion dollar acquisition while at the Office of Special Projects in Washington, D.C., and served as the Deputy Director of Logistics for the Joint Task Force supporting the military commissions in Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.\r\n\r\nPrior to her commission in the Navy she earned her Bachelor of Science in Industrial and Systems Engineering from Georgia Institute of Technology. During this time she studied at the National University of Singapore and Hong Kong University of Science and Technology. In April 2015 Maxine moved back to the DC area after completing a Master of Science degree in Operations Research at the Naval Postgraduate School in Monterey, CA.','Maxine Gardner','','publish','closed','closed','','maxine-gardner','','','2015-09-19 17:40:30','2015-09-19 21:40:30','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=178',0,'speaker','',0),(179,3,'2015-08-10 18:26:23','2015-08-10 22:26:23','','Katherine_Garcia','','inherit','closed','closed','','katherine_garcia','','','2015-08-10 18:26:30','2015-08-10 22:26:30','',175,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Katherine_Garcia.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(181,3,'2015-08-11 10:15:44','2015-08-11 14:15:44','','GabriellaZiccarelli','','inherit','closed','closed','','gabriellaziccarelli','','','2015-08-11 10:15:57','2015-08-11 14:15:57','',176,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/GabriellaZiccarelli.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(182,3,'2015-08-11 10:17:55','2015-08-11 14:17:55','','deb_tillet','','inherit','closed','closed','','bs-bs-bz-interview-tillet','','','2015-08-11 10:18:25','2015-08-11 14:18:25','',148,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DebTillett.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(185,3,'2015-08-16 19:37:38','2015-08-16 23:37:38','Coder / Speaker / Teacher / Writer.\r\n\r\nKatie is a Python and Django developer, with a touch of full-stack. She is also a noted speaker, having spoken at technical conferences all over the US. She often teaches classes in Python and accessibility. She writes for O\'Reilly and Pearson, and is working on her third book.','Katie Cunningham','','publish','closed','closed','','katie-cunningham','','','2015-09-18 12:05:00','2015-09-18 16:05:00','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=185',0,'speaker','',0),(186,3,'2015-08-14 13:05:54','2015-08-14 17:05:54','','Python 101 Hands On Workshop','','publish','closed','closed','','python-101-hands-on-workshop','','','2015-08-16 19:38:40','2015-08-16 23:38:40','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=186',0,'session','',0),(187,3,'2015-08-13 20:31:28','2015-08-14 00:31:28','','Jackie Albright','','publish','closed','closed','','jackie-albright','','','2015-08-14 11:25:13','2015-08-14 15:25:13','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=team&#038;p=187',0,'team','',0),(188,3,'2015-08-13 17:56:47','2015-08-13 21:56:47','','Jackie Albright','','inherit','closed','closed','','jackie-albright','','','2015-08-13 17:56:56','2015-08-13 21:56:56','',187,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Jackie-Albright.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(189,3,'2015-08-13 17:59:18','2015-08-13 21:59:18','','Margaret_Roth','','inherit','closed','closed','',