ff&amp;buyTicketsText=Buy Tickets\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>','Raleigh-Durham','','publish','closed','closed','','raleigh','','','2016-05-13 07:49:14','2016-05-13 11:49:14','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=260',0,'page','',0),(262,3,'2015-09-22 15:03:54','2015-09-22 19:03:54','<a href=\"https://www.thinkgeek.com/\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/thinkgeek.png\" alt=\"thinkgeek \" width=\"300\" height=\"40\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-263\" /></a>','THINKGEEK','','publish','closed','closed','','thinkgeek','','','2015-10-24 19:07:56','2015-10-24 23:07:56','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=sponsors&#038;p=262',0,'sponsors','',0),(263,3,'2015-09-22 15:03:18','2015-09-22 19:03:18','','thinkgeek','','inherit','closed','closed','','thinkgeek','','','2015-09-22 15:03:45','2015-09-22 19:03:45','',262,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/thinkgeek.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(269,3,'2015-10-11 17:52:55','2015-10-11 21:52:55',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','269','','','2015-10-18 21:16:39','2015-10-19 01:16:39','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?p=269',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(272,3,'2015-10-12 10:53:22','2015-10-12 14:53:22','','Washington Schedule','','publish','closed','open','','washington-schedule','','','2015-12-14 21:36:45','2015-12-15 02:36:45','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/washington-schedule/',0,'page','',0),(273,3,'2015-10-12 10:53:22','2015-10-12 14:53:22','','Washington Speakers','','publish','closed','open','','washington-speakers','','','2015-12-14 21:52:55','2015-12-15 02:52:55','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/washington-speakers/',0,'page','',2),(274,3,'2015-10-12 10:53:22','2015-10-12 14:53:22','Watch this space for more info','Washington Organizers','','publish','closed','open','','washington-organizers','','','2015-10-12 10:58:43','2015-10-12 14:58:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/washington-organizers/',0,'page','',0),(275,3,'2015-10-12 10:53:22','2015-10-12 14:53:22','','Washington Sponsors','','publish','closed','open','','washington-sponsors','','','2015-11-04 16:58:24','2015-11-04 21:58:24','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/washington-sponsors/',0,'page','',0),(276,3,'2015-10-12 10:53:22','2015-10-12 14:53:22','Sessions at the Women in Tech Summit cover a variety of topics spanning business,  technology and professional skills that will benefit everyone from programmers to executives, and focus on a broad range of tactical, technical, and strategic issues facing women today. Sessions will fall into one of the following tracks.\r\n<h4>Keynote or Closing Session</h4>\r\nEveryone has their own definition of personal success, however, common foundational elements are needed for individuals to build upon. Keynote and Closing Session topics will incorporate the theme of \"Rising Strong,\" the concept of populating your personal toolbox to achieve your definition of success.\r\n<h4>Rising Strong Track</h4>\r\nThe Rising Strong track provides audience members an opportunity to develop skills and learn from others related to what you need to get ahead. Potential topics include: leadership development, team dynamics, startup funding and investing, productivity, negotiation, marketing and branding, etc.\r\n<h4>Technology Trends Track</h4>\r\nThe Technology Trends track provides audience members an opportunity to learn more about a specific technology topic. Potential topics include: security, business intelligence, enterprise architecture, digital business, the Internet of Things, SaaS, data, etc.\r\n<h4>Hands-on Workshops</h4>\r\nHands-on workshops provide audience members with practical experience in a given topic. Attendees will be expected to have their own laptops to participate in the workshop. Potential topics include: mobile development, CSS3, HTML5, JavaScri