cisions… Big Data, Cloud Computing, Data Visualization, Mobile. These forces are converging, disrupting business models, and creating new opportunities.\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2014-speakers/\" target=\"_blank\">Speakers</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2014-sponsors/\" target=\"_blank\">Sponsors</a>\r\n</strong><strong><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2014-sessions/\" target=\"_blank\">Sessions</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2014-committee/\" target=\"_blank\">Committee Members</a></strong>\r\n<h1><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>2013 Event</strong></span></h1>\r\n<em>Summary:</em> April 20, 2013 - Philadelphia University<a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/wits2013closingsession.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-405 size-full\" src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/wits2013closingsession.jpg\" alt=\"wits2013closingsession\" width=\"240\" height=\"135\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Theme: “If You Only Knew”</strong>\r\n\r\nThe 2013 event featured keynote speakers and workshops addressing UX, Cloud, Mobility, App Development, Security, Social and Big Data. The theme was \"if you only knew\" and the goal was to make sure attendees knew what information, technology and partnerships are available to them and how far they can go with that knowledge.\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2013-speakers/\" target=\"_blank\">Speakers</a>\r\n</strong><strong><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2013-sponsors/\" target=\"_blank\">Sponsors</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2013-sessions/\" target=\"_blank\">Sessions</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2013-committee/\" target=\"_blank\">Committee Members</a></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>2012 Event</strong></span></h1>\r\n<em>Summary:</em> April 21, 2012 - Wharton School of Business, University of Pennsylvania\r\n\r\n<strong>Theme: “Getting In, Surviving, Thriving and Giving Back”</strong>\r\n\r\nThe inaugural Women in Tech Summit brought together women from many different facets of the technology industry to inspire, share, lean and connect with one another. Our event included a diverse schedule of panels, presentations and workshops led by some of the Philadelphia area’s most engaging women in tech.\r\n\r\nWhether you work in technology or are interested in joining the field, our speakers, instructors and networking opportunities will benefit you. More importantly, your experience and expertise mean you have something to share with the other women at the Women In Tech Summit! We encouraged all women, from students to experienced professionals to those getting back into the workforce, to be a part of the Women in Tech Summit.\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2012-speakers/\" target=\"_blank\">Speakers</a><a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/phillyWITSlogosm.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-404\" src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/phillyWITSlogosm.png\" alt=\"phillyWITSlogosm\" width=\"150\" height=\"133\" /></a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2012-sponsors/\" target=\"_blank\">Sponsors</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2012-sessions/\" target=\"_blank\">Sessions</a></strong>\r\n<strong> <a href=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/2012-committee/\" target=\"_blank\">Committee Members</a></strong>','Past Events','','publish','closed','closed','','past-events','','','2015-10-24 19:36:22','2015-10-24 23:36:22','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?page_id=328',0,'page