 and training with groups from 10 to 120 people. She spoke at sixteen conferences in seven countries on topics ranging from DevOps to User Story Mapping, improving effectiveness of distributed teams with retrospectives and agile games. She finds inspiration from reading, practicing yoga, hiking, traveling and spending time with her daughter Erica.&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,769,[null,0],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,4,0]\">\r\nActive member of global agile community, she has been volunteering at Agile Alliance conferences for the past 10 years. As a session reviewer and a submission coach, she provides guidance to prospective speakers and contributes to a program selection process at Agile Alliance and Scrum Alliance conferences. A member of “Women in Agile” group and NYC Scrum User group, she leads “Big Apple Scrum Day 2016” conference organizing initiative. Dana enjoys speaking, facilitating workshops and training with groups from 10 to 120 people. She spoke at sixteen conferences in seven countries on topics ranging from DevOps to User Story Mapping, improving effectiveness of distributed teams with retrospectives and agile games. She finds inspiration from reading, practicing yoga, hiking, traveling and spending time with her daughter Erica.</span>','Dana Pylayeva','','publish','closed','closed','','dana-pylayeva','','','2016-01-31 10:30:26','2016-01-31 15:30:26','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=624',0,'speaker','',0),(625,4,'2015-12-22 15:33:01','2015-12-22 20:33:01','Valerie Woolard is a software engineer. She holds bachelor\'s degrees in French and cognitive science from UC Berkeley and a master\'s degree in computer science from the University of Chicago. She is a member of Women Who Code DC and teaches coding classes with Girl Develop It DC. When she is not coding, Valerie can be found singing showtunes, running around DC and its environs, and chipping away at her ever-expanding list of books to read.','Valerie Woolard','','publish','closed','closed','','valerie-woolard','','','2016-01-12 07:11:06','2016-01-12 12:11:06','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=625',0,'speaker','',0),(626,6,'2015-12-22 15:41:53','2015-12-22 20:41:53','Leemay Nassery joined Comcast approximately five years ago as a Software Engineer. She’s worked on the web services and applications that orchestrate the On-Demand menu navigation for X1. Most recently she switched gears to focus on the \"big data\" side of the X1 platform. In her spare time, Leemay enjoys coaching and playing soccer.','Leemay Nassery','','publish','closed','closed','','leemay-nassery','','','2016-01-31 10:32:57','2016-01-31 15:32:57','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=626',0,'speaker','',0),(627,4,'2015-12-22 15:49:08','2015-12-22 20:49:08','Introduction to three practical functional programming languages. Scala and Clojure both hosted on the JVM so you have access to Java libraries, classes, etc. And Elixir leverging the Erlang JVM, specifically focusing on quick web applications development. We\'ll take a look at the initial struggles that went into learning each language, getting your local environment configured, syntax differences, etc.','The Functional Triumvirate: Scala, Elixir and Clojure','','publish','closed','open','','the-functional-triumvirate-scala-elixir-and-clojure','','','2016-02-22 21:29:25','2016-02-23 02:29:25','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=627',0,'session','',0),(628,4,'2015-12-22 15:52:50','2015-12-22 20:52:50','<span data-sheets-value=\"[null,2,&quot;Erica is an NYC fifth grader, curious about many things, including agile games and presentations she sees her mom designing. She is a big fan of Star Wars, Harry Potter and simulation games. Erica enjoys helping her mom to incorporate humorous references from both films into her agile presentations. She has been named the youngest speaker at Toronto Agile and Software conference in October 2015 where she co-facilitated a workshop and shared her experience applying user story mapping in non-technical context.&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,6659,[null,0],[null,2,16777215],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0,null,[null,2,2236962],&quot;arial, sans-serif&quot;]\">Erica is an NYC fifth grader, curious about many things, including agile games and presentations she sees her mom designing. She is a big fan of Star Wars, Harry Potter and simulation games. Erica enjoys helping her mom to incorporate humorous references from both films into her agile presentations. She has been named the youngest speaker at Toronto Agile and Software conference in October 2015 where she co-facilitated a workshop and shared her experience applying user story mapping in non-technical context.</span>','Erica Indman','','publish','closed','closed','','erica-indman','','','2016-01-31 10:31:14','2016-01-31 15:31:14','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=628',0,'speaker','',0),(629,4,'2015-12-22 15:56:07','2015-12-22 20:56:07','<span data-sheets-value=\"[null,2,&quot;No one wants to admit it, but working remote is hard. You have to collaborate with people you might never meet over a shoddy VPN connection with the added pressure of having non-stop productive days. ALL this while chasing the work-life balance unicorn. It\'s not easy, but it is doable. In this session, you\'ll learn how to play up your personal strengths to go the distance on a remote team. We\'ll also cover tips and techniques to get the most out of working remote and how to avoid common pitfalls like the &quot;freshman 40&quot;.&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,6723,[null,0],[null,2,16777215],null,null,null,null,0,null,null,0,null,[null,2,0],&quot;Arial&quot;]\">No one wants to admit it, but working remote is hard. You have to collaborate with people you might never meet over a shoddy VPN connection with the added pressure of having non-stop productive days. ALL this while chasing the work-life balance unicorn. It\'s not easy, but it is doable. In this session, you\'ll learn how to play up your personal strengths to go the distance on a remote team. We\'ll also cover tips and techniques to get the most out of working remote and how to avoid common pitfalls like the \"freshman 40\".</span>','Surviving Life as a Remote Web Worker','','publish','closed','open','','surviving-life-as-a-remote-web-worker','','','2016-02-22 21:29:26','2016-02-23 02:29:26','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=629',0,'session','',0),(630,4,'2015-12-22 15:58:59','2015-12-22 20:58:59','<span data-sheets-value=\"[null,2,&quot;Sara Cope is a project manager and developer with the U.S. federal government, operations guru at CSS-Tricks and co-founder &amp; instructor for Girl Develop It Dayton. She is a habitual volunteer and digital gov is her passion. As a lifelong midwesterner, she works remote from Dayton, Ohio. When Sara isn\\u2019t immersed in all things web, she can be found playing tabletop games and supporting her local park system.&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,6659,[null,0],[null,2,16777215],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0,null,[null,2,2236962],&quot;arial, sans-serif&quot;]\">Sara Cope is a project manager and developer with the U.S. federal government, operations guru at CSS-Tricks and co-founder &amp; instructor for Girl Develop It Dayton. She is a habitual volunteer and digital gov is her passion. As a lifelong midwesterner, she works remote from Dayton, Ohio. When Sara isn’t immersed in all things web, she can be found playing tabletop games and supporting her local park system.</span>','Sara Cope','','publish','closed','closed','','sara-cope','','','2016-01-31 10:34:08','2016-01-31 15:34:08','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=630',0,'speaker','',0),(631,4,'2015-12-22 17:02:18','2015-12-22 22:02:18','','Gabriella Ziccarelli JPG','','inherit','closed','closed','','gabriella-ziccarelli-jpg','','','2015-12-22 17:03:07','2015-12-22 22:03:07','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Gabriella-Ziccarelli-JPG.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(632,4,'2015-12-22 17:10:43','2015-12-22 22:10:43','<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Join Tiffany Li, Camille Stewart, Valerie Woolard, and Gabriella Ziccarelli in a panel discussion on the importance of building a balanced tech industry.  Discussion will cover topics such as:</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The value of having a balanced team (traditional and non traditional tech backgrounds)</li>\r\n	<li>How to build a workplace environment that is supportive of both traditional and non traditional tech teams - and why a balanced workforce will make your company more successful.</li>\r\n	<li>The importance of expanding the pool of potential co workers through non-degree bootcamps, more support for CS education, and varied tech job postings.</li>\r\n	<li>How those with non-traditional tech backgrounds can successfully \"hack\" their way in to the tech world.</li>\r\n	<li>How to identify, develop, and pitch your tech expertise and value add in the tech world</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: arial, sans, sans-serif;\">How to make bold career moves and own your career advancement - advocating for yourself, negotiating for what you deserve, and seizing opportunities to advance yourself as a woman in tech.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;','Driven, Diversified, & Dynamic: Building a Balanced Tech Industry','','publish','closed','open','','driven-diversified-dynamic-building-a-balanced-tech-industry','','','2016-02-22 21:29:26','2016-02-23 02:29:26','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=632',0,'session','',0),(633,5,'2015-12-22 20:59:00','2015-12-23 01:59:00','','amanda lange','','inherit','closed','closed','','amandalange','','','2015-12-22 21:15:05','2015-12-23 02:15:05','',592,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/amandalange.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(634,5,'2015-12-22 21:12:57','2015-12-23 02:12:57','','BeccaRefford','','inherit','closed','closed','','beccarefford','','','2015-12-22 21:13:18','2015-12-23 02:13:18','',585,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/BeccaRefford.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(635,5,'2015-12-22 21:17:50','2015-12-23 02:17:50','','Bobbie Carlton','','inherit','closed','closed','','bobbie-carlton-2','','','2015-12-22 21:17:56','2015-12-23 02:17:56','',600,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Bobbie-Carlton.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(636,5,'2015-12-22 21:22:50','2015-12-23 02:22:50','','DawnMcDougall','','inherit','closed','closed','','dawnmcdougall','','','2015-12-22 21:23:02','2015-12-23 02:23:02','',586,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/DawnMcDougall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(637,5,'2015-12-22 21:25:48','2015-12-23 02:25:48','','kristinmayneshayduk','','inherit','closed','closed','','kristinmayneshayduk','','','2015-12-22 21:26:24','2015-12-23 02:26:24','',607,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/kristinmayneshayduk.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(638,5,'2015-12-22 21:29:32','2015-12-23 02:29:32','','liverickson','','inherit','closed','closed','','liverickson','','','2015-12-22 21:29:50','2015-12-23 02:29:50','',608,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/liverickson.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(639,5,'2015-12-22 21:32:10','2015-12-23 02:32:10','','lizbrown','','inherit','closed','closed','','lizbrown','','','2015-12-22 21:32:17','2015-12-23 02:32:17','',588,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/lizbrown.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(640,5,'2015-12-22 21:34:33','2015-12-23 02:34:33','','loisbruckner','','inherit','closed','closed','','loisbruckner','','','2015-12-22 21:34:48','2015-12-23 02:34:48','',591,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/loisbruckner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(641,5,'2015-12-22 21:37:24','2015-12-23 02:37:24','','mavispogue','','inherit','closed','closed','','mavispogue','','','2015-12-22 21:37:38','2015-12-23 02:37:38','',589,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/mavispogue.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(642,5,'2015-12-22 21:39:51','2015-12-23 02:39:51','','melissahartz','','inherit','closed','closed','','melissahartz','','','2015-12-22 21:40:03','2015-12-23 02:40:03','',590,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/melissahartz.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(643,5,'2015-12-22 21:41:53','2015-12-23 02:41:53','','sinaepitts','','inherit','closed','closed','','sinaepitts','','','2015-12-22 21:42:10','2015-12-23 02:42:10','',609,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sinaepitts.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(644,4,'2015-12-24 08:36:58','2015-12-24 13:36:58','','Sara Cope','','inherit','closed','closed','','sara-cope-2','','','2015-12-24 08:37:06','2015-12-24 13:37:06','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Sara-Cope.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(646,5,'2015-12-25 16:16:42','2015-12-25 21:16:42','\"Do you see critical social needs in the community. Civic tech is all about using technology as a means of civic engagement to improve the place we live and bridge social gaps. Civic tech projects need skills of all kinds to be successful -- it\'s the shared values of civic participation that takes a civic tech project to a full civic tech app.\r\n\r\nCome to this workshop to learn the civic tech lifecycle from identifying a social need in the community to forming a project team. This is a hands-on workshop for all levels, no coding skills required, just come ready to brainstorm and get social!\"','Civic Tech: How Engaged Citizens Can Improve Cities','','publish','closed','open','','civic-tech-engaged-citizens-can-improve-cities','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=646',0,'session','',0),(647,5,'2015-12-25 16:18:33','2015-12-25 21:18:33','Prototyping is a great way to test ideas and assumptions, but you have to be smart about what to prototype and how much time and effort you want to put into it. Prototyping can speed time to market by reducing re-work, but if you aren’t careful it can increase time to market because you are creating prototypes instead of production-ready code. This intermediate level workshop will help you decide what to prototype, how prototyping can speed development up rather than slow it down, and learn more when you test.\r\n\r\nExercise 1 - Setting Expectations: Collaboratively establishing expectations for fidelity, functionality, content and data\r\nExercise 2 - Planning and Prioritizing: Learning how to pick the right problems to solve\r\nExercise 3 - Prototyping: Learning how to quickly create a prototype using sketches or a tool\r\nExercise 4 - Testing: Getting experience testing by grabbing people lingering in the hallway\r\nExercise 5 - Iterating: Deciding what’s next when it didn’t go the way you wanted\r\n','Use Prototyping to Get Good Faster','','publish','closed','open','','use-prototyping-to-get-good-faster','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=647',0,'session','',0),(648,5,'2015-12-25 16:21:44','2015-12-25 21:21:44','Can you tell the difference between a good user experience versus a bad one? Are you looking to learn more about how to become a UX Designer, or how to think like one? Join us to learn the basic principles of user experience and participate in a collaborative design exercise. \r\n\r\nKey Takeaways: \r\nLearn the principles of UX\r\nUnderstand UX related roles\r\nDiscover UX tools & resources\r\nParticipate in a hands-on collaborative design exercise\r\n','How to Think Like a UX Designer','','publish','closed','open','','how-to-think-like-a-ux-designer','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=648',0,'session','',0),(649,5,'2015-12-25 22:53:46','2015-12-26 03:53:46','Is it burn-out or is it time for a career change? Is your work dissatisfaction because of being you\'re in the wrong role, wrong industry or wrong career all together? This session will lead you through a self-assessment of your skill sets, abilities, how you like to work, what you have to offer, assets, and experiences. We hope you will leave refreshed and renewed!','Shifting Careers: Changing Gears or Changing Lanes','','publish','closed','open','','how-to-turn-your-career-around','','','2016-02-25 21:56:34','2016-02-26 02:56:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=649',0,'session','',0),(650,5,'2015-12-25 22:57:07','2015-12-26 03:57:07','A basic tenet in web standards today is the separation of the content (text, images, lists, and so on) from its presentation (formatting).  HTML structures the content of a web page while CSS defines the presentation of each element. The CSS Box Model defines how imaginary boxes exist around HTML elements, enabling you to format almost every aspect of how the box and its contents are rendered. This is the power of how CSS transforms web pages.\r\n\r\nKey Takeaways:\r\nRedefine the default settings of any HTML element using the CSS box model\r\nUse padding, margins, and borders to position content\r\nLearn the four main CSS concepts/theories that affect formatting text: cascade, inheritance, descendant and specificity theories\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nAn understanding of HTML is required. A laptop is required to participate in this workshop.','Understanding the Invisible Box (CSS)','','publish','closed','open','','understanding-the-invisible-box-css','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=650',0,'session','',0),(651,5,'2015-12-27 08:11:35','2015-12-27 13:11:35','Are you tired of sitting through yet another DAMP (Dreaded All Male Panel)? Your story will never be heard sitting in the audience. Being onstage is powerful but the issue with many women is that they don’t know how to get there. Join us as Bobbie Carlton, Founder of Innovation Women, a company that connects women with event managers looking for speakers, gives you the tools you need to get onstage, be heard, and be paid to speak!','No Excuses - How to Get Yourself on Stage','','publish','closed','open','','no-excuses-how-to-get-yourself-on-stage','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=651',0,'session','',0),(652,5,'2015-12-27 08:15:06','2015-12-27 13:15:06','Cybersecurity incidents continue to rise and cyber compromise is a matter of when, not if. The financial costs of a breach increase every year and today’s elevated threat environment has left most organizations wondering if they have already been (or soon will be) compromised. Many are deliberating how to strengthen their cybersecurity program, while others are scrambling to understand the motives of potential adversaries. For most businesses and users, the resolutions of these challenges are ambiguous, at best. This session will describe the current Cybersecurity landscape and the key components of effective programs and countermeasures for securing your company and yourself in today\'s digital world.','CyberSecurity -- A Deep Dive into Securing Your Company and Yourself in Today\'s Digital World','','publish','closed','open','','cybersecurity-a-deep-dive-into-securing-your-company-and-yourself-in-todays-digital-world','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=652',0,'session','',0),(653,5,'2015-12-27 08:22:32','2015-12-27 13:22:32','A staple of science fiction for decades, virtual and augmented reality technologies have begun to make their way into our own hands - experts estimate that by 2020, the VR and AR industry will be worth 150+ billion dollars. New content and devices are being released daily, resulting in an entirely new shift in the way we interact with technology. In this talk, we\'ll cover what it\'s like to find a path and navigate through the new frontier of modern computing within the virtual and augmented reality industry, and and how 3D immersive computing is already impacting industries around the globe.','Exploring the New Frontiers of Technology - Using Virtual Reality for More than Games','','publish','closed','open','','exploring-the-new-frontiers-of-technology-using-virtual-reality-for-more-than-games','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=653',0,'session','',0),(654,5,'2015-12-27 08:25:52','2015-12-27 13:25:52','SiNae started and grew a mobile development company over the past 6 years, earning the #31 spot on Philadelphia’s fastest growing companies list -- http://www.philadelphia100.com/.  Her presentation will focus on how she used her skills, experience and connections from her academic career and former job, to create a business that really suited her seemingly disparate collection of past roles and experiences, and how you can do the same.  SiNae will share the essential practices of being a “technology wrangler”, as she likes to call herself, including how she defined the \"Why\" or Mission of her company and how you can also define your Why. 	Technology Trends','How a Non-Technologist Started and Grew a Mobile Development Company','','publish','closed','open','','how-a-non-technologist-started-and-grew-a-mobile-development-company','','','2016-02-25 21:56:33','2016-02-26 02:56:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=654',0,'session','',0),(656,5,'2015-12-27 08:31:37','2015-12-27 13:31:37','Panel to discuss the multiple aspects of the Internet of Things in order to educate and inform the audience about this key Technological Trend.	','Internet of Things -- Exploring Many Aspects of a Key Technological Trend','','publish','closed','open','','internet-of-things-exploring-many-aspects-of-a-key-technological-trend','','','2016-02-25 21:56:34','2016-02-26 02:56:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=656',0,'session','',0),(657,3,'2015-12-27 08:42:10','2015-12-27 13:42:10','','arushisrivastava','','inherit','closed','closed','','arushisrivastava','','','2015-12-27 08:42:52','2015-12-27 13:42:52','',612,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/arushisrivastava.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(658,5,'2015-12-27 08:47:32','2015-12-27 13:47:32','As companies turn more and more to data for decision making, analysts need to be able to translate findings into visualizations that can be quickly, easily, and accurately understood. Attendees will leave the session with answers to their questions about principles of design, Tableau Software, and how to create engaging and effective presentations.	Ask the Experts','Beauty and Brains: Using Data Visualization to Effectively Communicate Your Data','','private','closed','closed','','beauty-and-brains-using-data-visualization-to-effectively-communicate-your-data','','','2016-01-15 14:48:15','2016-01-15 19:48:15','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=658',0,'session','',0),(665,6,'2016-01-02 23:06:49','2016-01-03 04:06:49','','LeemayNassery','','inherit','closed','closed','','leemaynassery','','','2016-01-02 23:06:49','2016-01-03 04:06:49','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/LeemayNassery.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(668,4,'2016-01-04 12:31:22','2016-01-04 17:31:22','','Jessica Bell','','inherit','closed','closed','','jessica-bell','','','2016-01-04 12:31:29','2016-01-04 17:31:29','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Jessica-Bell.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(669,4,'2016-01-05 10:02:50','2016-01-05 15:02:50','Jessica Bell is a Web Developer at RepEquity, a digital agency focusing on reputation management, online branding, and digital advocacy. She has a B.A. in International Relations from San Francisco State University and has worked all around the world. She started learning HTML, CSS, and WordPress in order to complete a website redesign and maintain the new site for her job as a digital media coordinator. Once hooked on learning code, she completed many tutorials, devoured endless books, attended a General Assembly Front End Development course, and eventually Jess landed a job as a Developer. She now works as a front end and Drupal developer, learning things every day from Git workflows, SASS, PHP, and JavaScript. She is a living example of going from no real tech experience to working professionally in the field and she loves every minute of her new role as a developer.\r\n\r\nThroughout this journey Jess has remained an active part of the DC Tech scene. She serves in a leadership role for DC FemTech and the DC Tech Meetup, and participates in the JavaScript Guild and Women Who Code. Jess has produced multiple events at RepEquity, including a hackathon, a panel on non-traditional pathways to tech, and training sessions on git and SASS.\r\n\r\nJess now works evenings as a teaching assistant for General Assembly’s Front End Development course teaching a new wave of developers! She tweets a lot about the ‪#‎noobDev‬ experience - follow her @sirjessthebrave!','Jessica Bell','','publish','closed','closed','','jessica-bell','','','2016-01-05 10:06:09','2016-01-05 15:06:09','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=669',0,'speaker','',0),(670,4,'2016-01-05 10:05:18','2016-01-05 15:05:18','This talk is aimed at those with a base knowledge of HTML and CSS. It will introduce the participants to modular thinking (breaking down a page/project into individual ‘modules’ to more easily re-use CSS code) and how SASS is a great way to apply modular thinking to CSS. It will show users how to get SASS setup, provide them with a SASS starter library, and go through basic variables, extendables, and mixins to start a SASS project. We will go through a ‘hello world’ web page to showcase the awesome power of SASS! I will also provide links/info on documentation, where to go in DC to learn SASS, and other helpful resources.','Scalable and Modular Architecture for CSS and Intro to Sass','','publish','closed','open','','scalable-and-modular-architecture-for-css-and-intro-to-sass','','','2016-02-22 21:29:26','2016-02-23 02:29:26','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=670',0,'session','',0),(671,4,'2016-01-05 10:44:17','2016-01-05 15:44:17','In this workshop, we will build a web application using the MEAN (MongoDB, Express, Angular, Node.js) Javascript stack. MongoDB is a NoSQL database with dynamic schemas and a document style database. NodeJS is an open source runtime environment that allows us to write Javascript server side with Express, a middleware available as a Node package that acts as the HTTP server and where we will write our API. Angular is a powerful client side Javascript framework that has two-way data binding which reduces the amount of effort that might be required with jQuery. This stack stands out from other types of architecture because the data stays the same from end to end – in Javascript and JSON. Literally, the object that is created in Angular can be directly posted via the API to MongoDB; no strict data typing or conversions required. This Javascript stack is amazing – with a little research, a person can start developing immediately!','When Being MEAN is a Good Thing: Developing with a Full Javascript Stack','','publish','closed','open','','when-being-mean-is-a-good-thing-developing-with-a-full-javascript-stack','','','2016-02-22 21:29:25','2016-02-23 02:29:25','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=671',0,'session','',0),(674,4,'2016-01-05 11:07:38','2016-01-05 16:07:38','','Cerner Logo','','inherit','closed','closed','','cerner-logo','','','2016-01-05 11:15:25','2016-01-05 16:15:25','',675,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Cerner-Logo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(675,4,'2016-01-05 11:13:52','2016-01-05 16:13:52','<a href=\"http://engineering.cerner.com/\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-674 alignleft\" src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Cerner-Logo-300x115.jpg\" alt=\"Cerner logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"115\" /></a>','Cerner','','publish','closed','closed','','cerner','','','2016-01-06 10:57:41','2016-01-06 15:57:41','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=sponsors&#038;p=675',0,'sponsors','',0),(677,4,'2016-01-06 18:45:46','2016-01-06 23:45:46','<span data-sheets-value=\"[null,2,&quot;In this panel discussion, you will hear from two leaders on their personal journeys, learn the science and facts behind why gender diversity is important in the workplace at all levels in an organization; and discuss as a group a set of best practices on how women can best support other women.&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,6659,[null,0],[null,2,16777215],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0,null,[null,2,2236962],&quot;arial, sans-serif&quot;]\">In this panel discussion, you will hear from two leaders on their personal journeys, learn the science and facts behind why gender diversity is important in the workplace at all levels in an organization; and discuss as a group a set of best practices on how women can best support other women.</span>','Women Helping Women: The Stories, the Science, and the Steps you can personally take to make a difference.','','publish','closed','open','','women-helping-women-the-stories-the-science-and-the-steps-you-can-personally-take-to-make-a-difference','','','2016-02-22 21:29:26','2016-02-23 02:29:26','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=677',0,'session','',0),(678,4,'2016-01-07 10:55:22','2016-01-07 15:55:22','','iStrategy Labs logo','','inherit','closed','closed','','isl-logo','','','2016-01-07 10:57:49','2016-01-07 15:57:49','',679,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ISL-Logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(679,4,'2016-01-07 11:34:04','2016-01-07 16:34:04','<a href=\"https://isl.co/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-678 alignleft\" src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ISL-Logo-300x199.png\" alt=\"iStrategy Labs\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>','iStrategy Labs','','publish','closed','closed','','istrategy-labs','','','2016-01-07 11:34:04','2016-01-07 16:34:04','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=sponsors&#038;p=679',0,'sponsors','',0),(680,3,'2016-01-07 17:16:54','2016-01-07 22:16:54','','cstewart','','inherit','closed','closed','','cstewart','','','2016-01-07 17:17:06','2016-01-07 22:17:06','',581,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cstewart.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(683,3,'2016-01-11 09:36:34','2016-01-11 14:36:34','','Women in Tech Summit Sponsorships PHL','','inherit','closed','closed','','women-in-tech-summit-sponsorships-phl','','','2016-01-11 09:36:34','2016-01-11 14:36:34','',294,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Women-in-Tech-Summit-Sponsorships-PHL.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(686,4,'2016-01-11 15:41:16','2016-01-11 20:41:16','<span data-sheets-value=\"[null,2,&quot;Faith Davis is the Director of Innovation &amp; Technology at DAF Technologies, a technology consulting firm, where she helps clients solves their biggest challenges through the use of emerging technology. We monitor emerging technologies and maintain strong relationships with start-ups, R&amp;D organizations in established companies, academic institutions, incubators, etc. This allows us to provide companies with insight on how to create competitive advantage, lower costs, or a new product or service. \\nShe works with Howard University professors and alumni to promote STEM based entrepreneurship and innovation. She is also a reviewer of early stage startup funding applications and a loaned executive to help startups reach their next significant milestone with Maryland Technology Development Corporation (TEDCO). \\n\\nPrior to DAF Technologies, Faith was a technology associate at In-Q-Tel a strategic venture capital firm where she focused on investments involving the mobile ecosystem. She owned the investment process from sourcing to deal close. She has over 13 years of experience in technology development, strategy, and venture capital. Faith has worked at NASA, Lawrence Livermore National Lab, and The MITRE Corporation. She has developed deep expertise in the areas of wireless communications, networking, mobile applications, devices, and internet companies. \\n\\nShe has published several technical papers and has been a speaker at technical conferences, technology focus days, commencements, women\\u2019s conferences, and affinity group meetings. This year, Faith was the 2015 Commencement Speaker for Howard University College of Engineering, Architecture, and Computer Science. Davis earned a B.S., summa cum laude, from Howard University and a M.S. from Stanford University in Electrical Engineering. \\n&quot;]\" data-sheets-userformat=\"[null,null,515,[null,0],[null,2,16777215],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,0]\">Faith Davis is the Director of Innovation &amp; Technology at DAF Technologies, a technology consulting firm, where she helps clients solves their biggest challenges through the use of emerging technology. We monitor emerging technologies and maintain strong relationships with start-ups, R&amp;D organizations in established companies, academic institutions, incubators, etc. This allows us to provide companies with insight on how to create competitive advantage, lower costs, or a new product or service.\r\nShe works with Howard University professors and alumni to promote STEM based entrepreneurship and innovation. She is also a reviewer of early stage startup funding applications and a loaned executive to help startups reach their next significant milestone with Maryland Technology Development Corporation (TEDCO).</span>\r\n\r\nPrior to DAF Technologies, Faith was a technology associate at In-Q-Tel a strategic venture capital firm where she focused on investments involving the mobile ecosystem. She owned the investment process from sourcing to deal close. She has over 13 years of experience in technology development, strategy, and venture capital. Faith has worked at NASA, Lawrence Livermore National Lab, and The MITRE Corporation. She has developed deep expertise in the areas of wireless communications, networking, mobile applications, devices, and internet companies.\r\n\r\nShe has published several technical papers and has been a speaker at technical conferences, technology focus days, commencements, women’s conferences, and affinity group meetings. This year, Faith was the 2015 Commencement Speaker for Howard University College of Engineering, Architecture, and Computer Science. Davis earned a B.S., summa cum laude, from Howard University and a M.S. from Stanford University in Electrical Engineering.','Faith Davis','','publish','closed','closed','','faith-davis','','','2016-01-11 15:45:17','2016-01-11 20:45:17','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpen