','image/jpeg',0),(737,4,'2016-01-29 21:29:16','2016-01-30 02:29:16','','Jessica Giannasca','','inherit','closed','closed','','jessica-giannasca-2','','','2016-01-29 21:35:59','2016-01-30 02:35:59','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Jessica-Giannasca.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(738,4,'2016-01-29 21:29:17','2016-01-30 02:29:17','','PegMeadow','','inherit','closed','closed','','pegmeadow','','','2016-01-29 21:30:07','2016-01-30 02:30:07','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/PegMeadow.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(739,4,'2016-01-29 21:29:18','2016-01-30 02:29:18','','GayleSmith','','inherit','closed','closed','','gaylesmith','','','2016-01-29 21:30:22','2016-01-30 02:30:22','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/GayleSmith.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(740,4,'2016-01-29 21:34:19','2016-01-30 02:34:19','Be our guest as five successful women from The Children’s Hospital of Philadelphia present a systematic roadmap for charting out your personal and professional goals – or “line of sight”. The panel will field topics such as creating an Individual Development Plan (IDP), embracing the uncertainty of a new role, and best practices on demonstrating leadership qualities, executive presence, and team building that will help you take control of your career path and navigate interesting opportunities.','Create Your Line of Sight - The Secret to Getting There is to Know Where You\'re Going','','publish','closed','open','','create-your-line-of-sight-the-secret-to-getting-there-is-to-know-where-youre-going','','','2016-02-25 21:56:34','2016-02-26 02:56:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=session&#038;p=740',0,'session','',0),(741,4,'2016-01-29 21:38:05','2016-01-30 02:38:05','Jessica Giannasca is the Interim Director of IS Business Operations at The Children’s Hospital of Philadelphia (CHOP). She leads the IS Business Operations department which includes IS Training, Business Continuity Management and IS Business Operations which runs the day to day operations of the Information Services Department with over 550 staff members. Jessica has proudly worked at CHOP for the last 12 years and has excelled in prior roles including Information Security Manager, Project Manager, Analyst, and Internal Auditor. She is a passionate driven leader and energetic communicator who creates strategic alliances with key leaders to achieve desired objectives. She strives to improve business process and obtain operational results while managing costs meticulously. She is also a mentor to staff and colleagues and finds fulfillment in building and retaining high performing teams of skilled professionals with high standards.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining CHOP, Jessica was a healthcare consultant at Protiviti helping various clients with HIPAA Security and Privacy rule compliance. She started her career as a Senior Associate at Arthur Andersen providing IT audit services and compliance assessments for her clients in various industries.\r\n\r\nJessica earned a Bachelor of Science in Accounting from Lehigh University and is a Certified Information Systems Auditor (CISA), Certified Internal Auditor (CIA) and Certified Information Security Manager (CISM).','Jessica Giannasca','','publish','closed','closed','','jessica-giannasca-2','','','2016-01-29 21:38:05','2016-01-30 02:38:05','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=741',0,'speaker','',0),(742,4,'2016-01-29 21:41:43','2016-01-30 02:41:43','Suzanne Gack, is an Information Services Strategist at The Children\'s Hospital of Philadelphia (CHOP). In this role, she develops IT strategies to lead the organization through a complex and ever changing healthcare environment. Suzanne has proudly worked at CHOP for the last 6 years by leading cross-functional complex programs to deploy the EHR, developing technology migration strategies for the Cardiac Center Complex and collaborating to support CHOP’s transition to value-based healthcare. Suzanne strives to improve the quality and safety in healthcare by building successful teams to achieve focused results and creative solutions. She is passionate about developing relationships to collaborate with customers on complex healthcare issues.\r\n\r\nIn May 2014, Suzanne received a Leadership Award for her exemplary commitment to CHOP’s IT performance for work on the Medical Device Integration Assessment. Her demonstration of leadership qualities enabled CHOP to successfully develop a long-term strategy to integrate medical device data, with the goal to improve the quality and safety of patient care for children. In addition to her work at CHOP, Suzanne serves on the Board of Directors for the Delaware Valley HIMSS chapter, where she leads as the Communications Chair.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining CHOP, Suzanne worked for a leading HIT Vendor – Siemens Healthcare for 23 years. She acquired extensive diversified knowledge in healthcare IT by excelling in multiple roles including Product Manager, Clinical Strategic Consultant, Integration Manager, Education Consultant and Clinical Implementation Analyst.','Suzanne Gack','','publish','closed','closed','','suzanne-gack-2','','','2016-01-29 21:41:43','2016-01-30 02:41:43','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=742',0,'speaker','',0),(745,4,'2016-01-29 21:51:41','2016-01-30 02:51:41','','KimberlyBurress','','inherit','closed','closed','','kimberlyburress','','','2016-01-29 21:51:53','2016-01-30 02:51:53','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/KimberlyBurress.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(747,4,'2016-01-29 22:43:04','2016-01-30 03:43:04','One of Forbes Top 10 Female Entrepreneurs to Watch and the mom of four boys, Founder of Colliders Accelerator, AboutOne (the world’s only Family Management Cloud Platform) and a board adviser to Flex-IT (an \"Uber for Tech contractors\"), Joanne Lang writes and speaks regularly on topics including entrepreneurship, fundraising, business development, networking, and leveraging technology to simplify life and prepare for the future.\r\n\r\nLang has appeared first on stage at VentureBeat DEMO and is one of the 3% of women who have raised $5M in capital in the US. She is and was featured in Microsoft’s documentary, CTRL+ALT+COMPETE. She’s a 2014 SmartCEO Voltage Award finalist, A Dell Founders Club Entrepreneur, and blogs for Huffington Post, The Wall Street Journal, Women 2.0, and Region’s Business. Lang is also a frequent panelist, including the NYU Women Entrepreneurs Festival, CES Living in Digital Times, Women 2.0 Founder <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_538667973\"><span class=\"aQJ\">Friday</span></span>, Women in Tech Summit, and BlogHer Entrepreneurs.  Lang is also a 2015 judge for \"The Stevie Awards\" for Women-In-Business.\r\n\r\nWith the support of AWE [<a href=\"http://www.phillyawe.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.phillyawe.org</a>] and Gartner, Joanne recently founded Colliders Accelerator, which offers a unique opportunity for women entrepreneurs’ to receive the customized mentoring they need to refine and launch their business ideas. The accelerator provides in-person and virtual educational sessions, as well as resources and funding assistance to build technology and run marketing and PR programs.  What really sets Colliders apart is their corporate matchmaking service that gives entrepreneurs an opportunity to find the perfect corporate business match and early access to customer revenue, investment or acquisition potential, while in-parallel providing a \"Virtual Innovation Center\" for corporations.','Joanne Lang','','publish','closed','closed','','joanne-lang-3','','','2016-01-29 22:43:04','2016-01-30 03:43:04','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=747',0,'speaker','',0),(749,4,'2016-01-29 22:50:46','2016-01-3