usiness Management from Tulane and Masters Certification in Security Management from Villanova. She holds the prestigious CISSP and CIPT professional certifications and is a member of ISC2, IAPP, ISSA, and OWASP. Cheryl enjoys providing cybersecurity awareness presentation to kids and their parents and presents through ISC2 “Safe and Secure Online” program.','Cheryl Carmel','','publish','closed','closed','','cheryl-carmel-2','','','2016-02-17 07:22:08','2016-02-17 12:22:08','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=796',0,'speaker','',0),(797,4,'2016-02-17 07:24:26','2016-02-17 12:24:26','','joan_soskin','','inherit','closed','closed','','joan_soskin','','','2016-02-17 07:24:33','2016-02-17 12:24:33','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/joan_soskin.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(798,4,'2016-02-17 07:30:09','2016-02-17 12:30:09','Joan Soskin lists \"Linchpin\" as her official role at BuLogics, Inc., an East Falls-based engineering/innovation firm that specializes in wireless communication, home automation, and building all the \"Things\" for the \"Internet of Things.\" Her experience with IoT dates back to her first project out of college, when she wrote a location-based program for barcode scanners mounted on forklift trucks in a distribution warehouse; most recently, she founded, served as CEO, and built a software platform for a startup that pioneered proximity-based technology using iBeacons to encourage interactivity in museums.\r\n\r\nAt BuLogics, Joan’s role spans everything from product development and engineering to business development. Day-to-day, she leads Agile teams to build products that range from integrated connected lock systems to smart countertop gardening to app-enabled thermostats. Drawing on experiences as both product manager and cross-platform developer, Joan wants to build an intelligent world through smarter devices. She is a graduate of the Flatiron School and Duke U