r control of your site, and frees you from some of WordPress\' limitations. This talk is for intermediate-level WordPress users, and is intended to be a jumping-off point for further PHP development.\n\n<strong>Key Takeaways:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Working in the functions.php file of your site</li>\n	<li>Registering custom post types there using a text editor of your choice, or WordPress\' on-site PHP editor</li>\n	<li>Adding your custom post type to your navigation bar</li>\n	<li>Creating a single-page and archive-page (think blog-style format) for your custom post type</li>\n	<li>Customizing these pages within the Loop by using display functions</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Planning to attend PHP workshop? First, you\'ll need to get access to the files that make up your site. </strong>\n\nThe process of doing this is called SFTP, or Safe File Transfer Protocol. It\'s how you get into the guts of your website.\n\n<strong>Install SFTP client on your laptop prior to workshop. Do not wait to install this during the workshop.</strong>\n• CyberDuck https://cyberduck.io/?l=en\n• Filezilla Client https://filezilla-project.org/\nSuccessfully connect at least one time to webhost prior to workshop.\n\n<strong>Here are 2 sample tutorials for getting started.</strong>\n<a href=\"https://mediatemple.net/community/products/dv/204643960/using-filezilla-for-ftp-sftp\" target=\"_blank\">https://mediatemple.net/community/products/dv/204643960/using-filezilla-for-ftp-sftp</a>\n<a href=\"https://wpengine.com/support/sftp/\" target=\"_blank\">https://wpengine.com/support/sftp/</a>\n\n<em>Feel free to Google more if they don\'t help you.</em>\n\n<strong>Here\'s the general idea of how to proceed:</strong>\n• Ask your webhost for proper credentials (Port, IP address, your username, and your password).\n• Test them in your FTP client.\n• If it\'s a success, a window will open listing each of the files of your site.\n• Create a new folder in your home directory, name it whatever you want to call your new project. Let\'s call it \'WITSPHP\'\n• Drag your wp-content folder from your SFTP window to the \'WITSPHP\' file.\n• Open \'WITSPHP\' in your favorite text editor*\n• You\'re ready for the workshop!\n\n<strong>*Selecting a Text Editor-Resource list</strong>\n<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/Learn/Common_questions/Available_text_editors\" target=\"_blank\">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/Learn/Common_questions/Available_text_editors</a>\n<a href=\"http://webdesign.tutsplus.com/articles/free-course-choosing-a-text-editor--cms-24510\" target=\"_blank\">http://webdesign.tutsplus.com/articles/free-course-choosing-a-text-editor--cms-24510</a>\n\nGet Desktop Server: \nhttps://serverpress.com/\n\nResources from Presentation:\n<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/14-wJyTQ1ZGQ5c4gMt-zA78lnaSw39_VbWi6gWR_86S0/edit\">Plugin text file</a> \n<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1oJJSrVlJXfRTMMB0_4URcQizktXNUMoxBvdL-BAIoG0/edit?ts=56ffcb3c#slide=id.p\">Slides from Becca</a>\nhttps://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1oJJSrVlJXfRTMMB0_4URcQizktXNUMoxBvdL-BAIoG0/edit?ts=56ffcb3c#slide=id.p\n\n\n','Practical PHP: How to Back Away Slowly from Your WordPress Dashboard','','inherit','closed','closed','','563-autosave-v1','','','2016-04-09 12:08:14','2016-04-09 16:08:14','',563,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/563-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(948,1,'2016-03-22 14:25:21','2016-03-22 18:25:21','','Order &ndash; March 22, 2016 @ 02:25 PM','','wc-completed','closed','closed','order_56f18e11bfb5e','order-mar-22-2016-0625-pm','','','2016-04-07 17:34:51','2016-04-07 21:34:51','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=948',0,'shop_order','',4),(950,1,'2016-03-22 18:10:37','2016-03-22 22:10:37','','Order &ndash; March 22, 2016 @ 06:10 PM','','wc-completed','closed','closed','order_56f1c2dd404b3','order-mar-22-2016-1010-pm','','','2016-04-07 17:34:34','2016-04-07 21:34:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpe