tion issues, and more.\n2) Next, we\'ll do some browser-hacking and see what websites record about our actions. We\'ll also attempt to carry out some script-based exploits manually.\n3) We\'ll do some cursory scanning and recon of our target, including operating system and application fingerprinting.\n4) Finally, we\'ll use OWASP ZAP to automate some attacks, attempt to hack a password, and send some spam.\n\n\n','Security Tools So Simple Your Grandma Could Hack You!','','inherit','closed','closed','','578-autosave-v1','','','2016-04-07 16:15:46','2016-04-07 20:15:46','',578,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/578-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1000,4,'2016-04-27 08:23:41','2016-04-27 12:23:41','<a href=\"http://rtp.org\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-970 alignleft\" src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/RTP.Logo_.edited-300x163.png\" alt=\"RTP\" width=\"300\" height=\"163\" /></a>','Research Triangle Park','','publish','closed','closed','','research-triangle-park','','','2016-05-02 10:48:34','2016-05-02 14:48:34','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=sponsors&#038;p=1000',0,'sponsors','',0),(1002,3,'2016-05-10 12:13:18','2016-05-10 16:13:18','<a href=\"https://www.metlife.com/products/index.html\"><img src=\"http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/MetLife_logo.png\" alt=\"MetLife logo\" width=\"500\" height=\"114\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1004\" /></a>','MetLife','','publish','closed','closed','','metlife','','','2016-05-10 12:13:18','2016-05-10 16:13:18','',0,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/?post_type=sponsors&#038;p=1002',0,'sponsors','',0),(1004,3,'2016-05-10 12:12:48','2016-05-10 16:12:48','','MetLife_logo','','inherit','closed','closed','','metlife_logo','','','2016-05-10 12:13:02','2016-05-10 16:13:02','',1002,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/MetLife_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1005,4,'2016-05-11 14:08:30','2016-05-11 18:08:30','Sessions at the Women in Tech Summit cover a variety of topics spanning business,  technology and professional skills that will benefit everyone from programmers to executives, and focus on a broad range of tactical, technical, and strategic issues facing women today. Sessions will fall into one of the following tracks.\r\n<h4>Keynote or Closing Session</h4>\r\nEveryone has their own definition of personal success, however, common foundational elements are needed for individuals to build upon. Keynote and Closing Session topics will incorporate the theme of \"Rising Strong,\" the concept of populating your personal toolbox to achieve your definition of success.\r\n<h4>Rising Strong Track</h4>\r\nThe Rising Strong track provides audience members an opportunity to develop skills and learn from others related to what you need to get ahead. Potential topics include: leadership development, team dynamics, startup funding and investing, productivity, negotiation, marketing and branding, etc.\r\n<h4>Technology Trends Track</h4>\r\nThe Technology Trends track provides audience members an opportunity to learn more about a specific technology topic. Potential topics include: security, business intelligence, enterprise architecture, digital business, the Internet of Things, SaaS, data, etc.\r\n<h4>Hands-on Workshops</h4>\r\nHands-on workshops provide audience members with practical experience in a given topic. Attendees will be expected to have their own laptops to participate in the workshop. Potential topics include: mobile development, CSS3, HTML5, JavaScript, WordPress, open source, user experience, design thinking, Python, Ruby on Rails, etc.','Raleigh Schedule','','inherit','closed','closed','','276-autosave-v1','','','2016-05-11 14:08:30','2016-05-11 18:08:30','',276,'http://womenintechs.staging.wpengine.com/276-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
